(2, 1, 'A Dragon''s Ascension', '', 0, 1, 12, 20.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Book 3</strong> of <em>The Band of Four </em>series.</p>\r\n<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Band of Four</em> continue their battle for good: <em>Hawkril,</em> a bold and brave warrior gifted with great strength and fortitude; <em>Craer,</em> the crafty and clever thief; <em>Sarasper</em>, the learned and wise healer; and <em>Lady Embra Silvertree</em>, a powerful sorceress.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In <strong>Book 1</strong>: <em>The Kingless Land</em>, high magic and wizard kings stood in the way.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In <strong>Book 2</strong>: <em>The Vacant Throne,</em> civil wars and backstabbing barons resisted the restoration of order. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Now, in <strong>Book 3</strong>, the legendary Sleeping King has been restored to the throne through the efforts of the Band of Four, but peace has not returned.&nbsp; A powerful warlord comes to the front to take control of Aglirta through military might, while the diabolic minions of the Serpent move into position for a climactic battle that will scar the Band of Four forever.<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Booklist: </strong><em>&ldquo;The originality and wit [Greenwood] displayed in his previous work is even more evident in this saga, and indeed there is little that is generic about any aspect of either this book or the series of which it is a part.&rdquo;</em><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kirkus Reviews:</strong> "Greenwood&rsquo;s nimble fingers hurtle through castles and stone hallways: a rousing return."</p>', '', '978-0-7861-3121-1', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3, 1, 'A Field of Darkness', '', 0, 1, 11, 20.95, 1, '', '<p><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A venomously witty portrait of a fallen high society girl turned fledgling detective when she tries to solve a 20 year old murder.<br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When the name of her favorite cousin is linked to a brutal 20 year old unsolved murder, Madeline&rsquo;s investigations trigger a string of grisly new murders and the trail of blue blood legendary vindictiveness leads right up to her door.<br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Unwilling to turn her evidence over to the authorities before figuring some things out herself, she embarks on an ill-prepared and harrowing investigation into the dark side of her rich family world.<br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The case is dubbed the <em>"Rose Girls</em>&rdquo; for the thorny crown encircling the two young hippies found murdered. Madeline&rsquo;s preposterously preppy cousin, Lapthorne Townsend, becomes a suspect when his army dog tags are found at the scene of the crime. But she believes him just another clueless rich far too feckless to engage in foul play.<br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bent on exonerating him, she sets out to retrace the <em>Rose Girls</em>&rsquo; final hours, embarking on an ill-prepared and harrowing investigation into the dark side of her rich family&rsquo;s world.<br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Narrator, <em>Hillary</em><em> Huber</em>, excels portraying the main character&rsquo;s shotgun-toting attitude, her husband&rsquo;s farm family expressions and the snobbishness of upper crust society. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Booklist - Starred Review:</span></strong><em><span lang="EN-US">"Every page is a pleasure in this mystery debut featuring barb-wielding, ex-debutante Madeline Dare... Read&rsquo;s plot crackles and pops, but her characters steal the show. <br />"Among them: a shifty-eyed silhouettist, a lustful livestock auctioneer, and in-laws who make the cast of Deliverance seem urbane. <br />"This is sure to be loved by fans of comic mysteries, but don&rsquo;t be surprised if Tom Wolfe readers are equally smitten by Read&rsquo;s venomously witty portrait of a fallen WASP."</span></em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong><span lang="EN-US">Publishers Weekly: </span></strong><em><span lang="EN-US">&ldquo;Consistently delights. The author&rsquo;s sharp social commentary on everything from the idle rich to the environment adds to the pleasure.&rdquo;<br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></span></em><strong><span lang="EN-US">Kirkus Reviews - Starred Review:</span></strong><em><span lang="EN-US"> "Read&rsquo;s sensational debut features spot-on descriptions of upstate-downstate conflicts, strong characterizations and a fascinating plot."</span></em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(4, 1, 'A License to Steal', '', 0, 1, 7, 16.95, 1, '', '<p><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This is not your everyday "cops and robbers" story... more fascinating! <br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; As early as the 1940s, <em>Walter</em><em> L. Shaw</em> was thinking of speakerphones, conference calls, and call forwarding. Of the 39 patents to his credit, those three telephonic breakthroughs were his biggest inventions, yet nobody knows his name. <br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ahead of the world by decades, Shaw spent a lifetime inventing and patenting the many means of communication we take for granted, but he was repeatedly cheated by shrewd businessmen and big corporations. <br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Along comes Jr.,&nbsp;enraged by the ill treatment of his father and embraced a personal mission to even the score. <br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This book is the story of how Shaw Jr. became one of the most prolific jewel thieves in U.S. history, while Shaw Sr., in order to make ends meet for his family, was persuaded to put his brilliance to work for the mob. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"> <em>&ldquo;The Narrator, <strong>Joe Barrett</strong> does a good wise-guy impression, telling the story of Walter T. Shaw, an unrepentant jewel thief and mobster. Barrett does a good "Moustache Pete" and an excellent Sicilian."</em></span></p>', 'Holis ola k ase?', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(5, 1, 'Allan Quartermain', '', 0, 1, 12, 20.95, 1, '', '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Allan Quatermain,</em> in the late 1800s, was an English-born professional big game hunter and occasional trader in southern Africa who supported colonial efforts to spread civilization and native Africans having a say in how their affairs are run. He became a quintessential imperial outdoorsman who rejected the English cities and found its climate unbearable, and thus preferred to spend most of his life in Africa.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thrilled by rumors of a lost civilization, three Englishmen decide to travel to the heart of Africa with their Zulu guide, where they meet with continual peril: an attack by a cruel warrior tribe, the scorch of underground volcanic fires, and an encounter with a huge species of ferocious black crab.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exhausted and depleted of supplies, the men at last arrive at a mysterious city in the highlands of the interior.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The people, called the Zu-Vendi, enjoy a civilization suggesting Egyptian origin, which includes a sun-worshiping priesthood. The travelers immediately fall into disfavor with the priests by shooting some sacred hippopotami.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; More problems arise when Sir Henry falls in love with one of the twin queens who rule the land. Her devious sister becomes jealous, and civil war erupts.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Written in 1887, this sequel to <em>King Solomon&rsquo;s Mines</em> is filled with the spirit of adventure (also here at <em>www.MundoHablado.com</em>).<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; KLIATT:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Williams&rsquo;s fully voiced reading of this magnificent first-person narrative emphasizes the dangers and hardships that the adventurers undergo in their journey. Williams reads with excellent narrative timing, and his wide range of voices and accents adds a great deal</em>."</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(6, 1, 'American Gangster', '', 0, 1, 10, 19.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This vivid journalistic expose was the basis for the Universal Pictures&rsquo; release, <em>American Gangster</em>, starring Denzel Washington and <em>Russell Crowe.</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No one ever paid much attention to Frank Lucas, the quiet limo driver of one of the Black mobsters in New York. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; But when his boss meets an unexpected death, Frank takes the chance to fill the vacuum in the underground power structure to build his own empire and realize his own version of the American Dream.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thanks to his innate leadership qualities and a ruthless operational ethic, he takes control of the drug traffic in the Big Apple flooding the streets with higher quality/lower priced heroin smuggled from the East in the coffins of dead soldiers from Vietnam. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the 1970s, Frank Lucas was the king of the Harlem drug trade, bringing in over a million dollars a day. He lived a glamorous life, hobnobbing with athletes, musicians, and politicians, but Lucas was a ruthless gangster. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In <em>American Gangster</em>, Mark Jacobson&rsquo;s captivating account of the life of Frank Lucas joins other tales of New York City from the past thirty years. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The collection features a number of Jacobson&rsquo;s most famous essays, as well as previously unpublished works and more recent articles. Together, they create a vibrant, many-layered portrait of the most fascinating city in the world, by one of the most acclaimed journalists of our time.</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(7, 1, 'Black Wave', '', 0, 1, 8, 16.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:</strong> <em>A Family&rsquo;s Adventure at Sea and the Disaster That Saved Them</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recently a documentary aired in the <em>&ldquo;I Shouldn&rsquo;t Be Alive&rdquo; Animal Planet T</em><em>V</em><em> </em>series about the true survival story told in this audiobook.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A jaw dropping true tale of a high seas encounter with one of nature&rsquo;s most harrowing events...<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When <em>John </em>and <em>Jean Silverwood</em>, both experienced sailors, decided to give their four children a taste of life on the high seas, they hoped the trip would offer important learning experiences, not only about the natural world but about the beauty of human life stripped down to its essence, far from civilization.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; But the adventure that awaited them would surpass anything they could have imagined.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Aboard their 55-foot catamaran, the <em>Silverwood</em> family found its bonds tested as never before as they struggled with family and marriage dynamics in compressed quarters alongside the terrifying forces of nature.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the crucible of the sea, a stronger, tighter unit was forged. Then, just when it seemed that they had mastered every challenge, their world was shattered in a split second of sheer horror.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Now the real test began, forcing them to fight for their very lives.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Carrington MacDuffie expresses Jean&rsquo;s excitement at global scenic spots, her pride in son Ben&rsquo;s growing maturity, and her disappointment at her husband&rsquo;s slips from sobriety</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "Joe Barrett, <em>as John, picks up the story with the aftermath of the crash....He is husky-voiced and volatile....<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "Both Narrators deliver foreign accents well, and their dual reading makes this loosely organized adventure tale special.&rdquo;</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(8, 1, 'Blood Diamonds', '', 0, 1, 7, 16.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:</strong> <em>Tracing the Deadly Path of the World&rsquo;s Most Precious Stones<br /><br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The 2006 movie <em>Blood Diamonds</em> with <em>Leonardo DiCaprio</em> and <em>Jennifer Connelly</em>, was based on this book.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Discover the international diamond trail of brutality, horror and profit... a story of global consequences! <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A &ldquo;<em>conflict diamond</em>&rdquo; is one that is mined illegally by groups trying to overthrow the legitimate governments of certain countries. The profits from these stolen mines are used to continue funding for their brutal, murderous military actions.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This is one of these gripping stories of blood diamonds by Greg Campbell.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the 90s, the country of Sierra Leone was under terrible civil war between the legitimate government and the Revolutionary United Front (RUF) a group that had no real ideology other than takeover of the government, money, and according to Campbell, the diamond fields of the country. They did so in a horribly violent way.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Award-winning journalist Greg Campbell traces the deadly trail of these diamonds and the repercussions felt far beyond the poor and war-ridden country of Sierra Leone.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp; New York Times:</strong> &ldquo;Mr. Campbell tells this complex tale from a personal, feet-on-the ground perspective....He reminds us that there is no longer any such thing as an isolated conflict that governments and corporations can ignore with impunity.&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Washington Times:</strong> &ldquo;A vivid, hair-raising tale of brutal proportions that outdistances any fictional tale of derring-do.&rdquo; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>AudioFile: </strong>&ldquo;Though he steps into the vocal cadence of African leaders, Tom Weiner wisely doesn&rsquo;t overdramatize. His pace, clarity, and compelling tone work to keep listener attention throughout a detailed explanation of how the diamond market works."</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9, 1, 'Callahan''s Legacy', '', 0, 1, 7, 13.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The most famous bar in all space-time is going to rock tonight... Impossible to listen to without having fun!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lovable storyteller and bartender <em>Jake Stonebender</em>, gradually introduces the large cast of oddball drunks and barflies who inhabit the Long Island tavern known as <em>M</em>ary&rsquo;s Place.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The regulars include at least one alien, an Artificial Intelligence, a supernatural being or two and a talking dog named <em>Ralph Von Wau Wau.<br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></em>As usual, a couple of new oddballs wander into the bar to tell their stories. Then a crisis arises!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; On this particular day, nothing seems to be going right for<em> Stonebender</em>&rsquo;s.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; First a huge storm rips the roof off the bar&mdash;and moments later, drops another, better roof on it.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Then, <em>Mary Callahan</em> and her husband show up, unconscious, literally out of nowhere, and they bring bad news to the barfolk: a nasty three-eyed, three-toed, three-everythinged purple monster is going to descend upon them within mere hours.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The boys soon take care of the situation, however, by drinking a lot of beer and Irish coffee, telling jokes and not losing their cool.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Amazon:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Spider Robinson</em>, <em>whose cutting wit and keen insights are in full force, takes the opportunity to dive deep into the psyche of his various mainstay characters, making for some darkly intimate reading</em>.&rdquo;<strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</strong> &ldquo;Robinson <em>orchestrates the fast-paced wit and general banter, moving easily among his broad cast of eccentric characters....His presentation of this eclectic group of characters will make followers of his work feel welcome and newcomers feel they have found a unique and friendly place to hang out.</em>&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Publishers Weekly:</strong> &ldquo;<em>What</em> Robinson&rsquo;s<em> many fans look for above all is humor, wordplay, and a complicated web of allusions to favorite rock lyrics, classic Science Fiction stories and previous Callahan tales. They get plenty of each here and should feel right at home, again</em>.&rdquo;</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(10, 1, 'Che Guevara', '', 0, 1, 37, 44.95, 1, '', '<p><strong><span lang="EN-US">Subtitle:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"> <em>A Revolutionary Life</em> <br /><br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This acclaimed US bestseller chronicles the life of the dashing rebel from Argentina, Che Guevara, whose epic dream was to end poverty and injustice in the third world through armed revolution.</span><span lang="EN-US"><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; From his comfortable Argentine upbringing to the battlefields of the Cuban revolution, from the halls of power in Castro&rsquo;s government to his failures in the Congo and ultimately his assassination in the Bolivian jungle.</span><span lang="EN-US"><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Through exclusive access to previously unavailable personal archives, government documents and rare interviews, the author reveals many aspects of Che&rsquo;s life long cloaked in secrecy and intrigue. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"> <em>&ldquo;Excellent....admirably honest staggeringly researched....It is unlikely that after Anderson&rsquo;s exhaustive contribution, much more will be learned about Guevara.&rdquo;</em></span><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong><span lang="EN-US">Los Angeles</span></strong><strong><span lang="EN-US"> Times:</span></strong><em><span lang="EN-US"> &ldquo;An enduring achievement. It is hard to imagine that any will match the volume and detail of the research here.... victories and failures, equally spectacular, are part of our common history&hellip;.Che lives, not only in this book, but in the world.&rdquo;</span></em><strong><span lang="EN-US"><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; New York Times Book Review:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"> <em>&ldquo;A sweeping biography of the Latino revolutionary and pop-culture hero....Anderson paints a portrait of Guevara as both hero and fanatic....Students of Che&rsquo;s life and deeds need look no farther than Anderson&rsquo;s volume.&rdquo;</em></span><strong><span lang="EN-US"><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Boston Globe:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"> <em>&ldquo; exceptional and exciting biography....Anderson&rsquo;s up-close look, with beauty marks and tragic flaws so effortlessly rendered, brings the reader face to face with a man whose &rsquo;unshakable faith in his beliefs was made more powerful by his unusual combination of romantic passion and a coldly analytical mind.&rsquo;...an invaluable addition to the literature of American revolutionaries.&rdquo;</em></span></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11, 1, 'Cleopatra', '', 0, 1, 12, 20.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:</strong> <em>Being an Account of the Fall and Vengeance of Harmachis, the Royal Egyptian, As Set Forth by His Own Hand<br /><br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The sight of <em>Cleopatra&rsquo;</em>s beauty strikes the young Egyptian with all the power of a mortal blow. And for a moment Harmachis aches with grief because he has to kill someone so lovely!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rider Haggard&rsquo;s <em>Cleopatra</em>, first published in 1889, is an adventure story set in the Ptolemaic era of ancient Egypt.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Egyptian priesthood attempts to overthrow Queen <em>Cleopatra</em> in order to drive out the Romans and restore Egypt to a golden age.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It is written from the point of view of Harmacis at the end of his life. Like so many others he was obsessed with the beautiful <em>Cleopatra</em>, and so he tells her story as much as his.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; As youngster, he is sent on a mission, but the sight of <em>Cleopatra</em>&rsquo;s beauty in her sleep bewitches the young Egyptian and he cannot complete the task.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Unlike most of her admirers, Harmachis actually gets involved with Cleopatra. She pushes him to reveal secrets of Isis (including the location of hidden treasures of the pyramids) to further her political ends.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Did<em> Cleopatra</em> truly loved the low class priest or was he just another stepping stone for her ambition?<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The story is timeless in its portrayal of issues such as love and betrayal, love vs religion.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; With the right blend of action, emotion and the awesome well researched lifestyle of the Egyptian pharaohs, it is a memorable and gripping story.<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Reviewer&rsquo;s Bookwatch:</strong> &ldquo;<em>This outstanding, unabridged audiobook edition of Cleopatra is ably narrated by William Sutherland and is technically flawless in its recording</em>.&rdquo;</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(12, 1, 'Crime and Punishment', '', 0, 1, 21, 31.95, 1, '', '<p><em>Crime and Punishment</em> is an intense psychological study, a terrifying murder mystery, and a fascinating detective thriller instilled with philosophical, religious, and social commentary.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A desperate young man plans the perfect crime -- the murder of a despicable pawnbroker, an old women no one loves and no one will mourn.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Is it not just, he reasons, for a man of genius to commit such a crime, to transgress moral law -- if it will ultimately benefit humanity? So begins one of the greatest novels ever written.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Raskolnikov, an impoverished student living in a garret in the gloomy slums of St. Petersburg, carries out his grotesque scheme and plunges into a hell of persecution, madness and terror.<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>AudioFile:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Anthony Heald</em> <em>shows remarkable versatility in this production....he delivers the dialogue as a stage actor would, with exaggerated emotion and even with laughter, coughing, stammering, and other adornments indicated in the text....Heald&rsquo;</em><em>s pacing and rich characterizations keep the story moving.&rdquo; <br /></em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Merriam-Webster Encyclopedia of Literature:</strong> "<em>Dostoevsky&rsquo;s first masterpiece....A moving depiction of the recovery of a man&rsquo;s diseased spirit."</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(13, 1, 'Dancing in the Streets', '', 0, 1, 10, 19.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:<em> </em></strong><em>A History of Collective Joy</em><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; From best-selling social commentator and cultural historian Barbara Ehrenreich comes this fascinating exploration of one of humanity&rsquo;s oldest traditions: the celebration of communal joy, historically expressed in ecstatic revels of feasting, costuming, and dancing.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ehrenreich uncovers the origins of communal celebration in human biology and culture, showing that such mass festivities have been indigenous to the West since the ancient Greeks.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Though suppressed by elites who fear the undermining of social hierarchies, outbreaks of group revelry still persist as Ehrenreich shows, pointing to the 1960s rock-and-roll rebellion and the more recent &ldquo;carnivalization&rdquo; of sports.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Original, exhilarating, and deeply optimistic, Dancing in the Streets shows that we are innately social beings, impelled to share our joy and thereby envision a peaceable future.<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Publishers Weekly: </strong>&ldquo;Ehrenreich writes with grace and clarity in a fascinating, wide-ranging and generous account.&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp; KLIATT:</strong> &ldquo;This book is remarkably well researched and detailed, and Ward reads it like a college professor in a clear, well modulated voice. Anyone interested in dance will be fascinated by the examples and stories.&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Kirkus Reviews:</strong> &ldquo;A serious look at communal celebrations, well documented and presented with assurance and flair.&rdquo;</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(14, 1, 'Death by Black Hole', '', 0, 1, 12, 22.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:</strong> <em>....and other Cosmic Quandaries<br /><br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of the<strong> </strong><em>AudioFile Earphones Award</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong>Learn in a humorous way about black holes, dwarf planets, Lagrangian points, intelligent design, galactic gas clouds, quasars.. and all that jazz! <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In 2007, <em>Tyson</em>, who is known for his colorful character, cheerful demeanor, and obvious awe of the vastness of the universe, was chosen to be a regular on <em>The History Channel&rsquo;s</em> new series <em>The Universe</em>, which has proven to be a popular series.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tyson introduces us to the physics of black holes by explaining what would happen to our bodies if we fell into one, examines the needless friction between science and religion, and notes Earth&rsquo;s progression to &ldquo;an insignificantly small speck in the cosmos.&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Renowned for his ability to blend content, accessibility, and humor, <em>Tyson</em> is a natural teacher who simplifies some of the most complex concepts in astrophysics while sharing his infectious excitement for our universe.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Readers of Natural History magazine will be familiar with many of the 42 essays collected here, while newcomers will profit from Tyson&rsquo;s witty and entertaining description of being pulled apart atom by atom into a black hole, and other closer-to-earth, and cheerier, topics.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Library Journal:</strong> <em>"Demonstrates a good feel for explaining science in an intelligible way to interested lay readers; his rather rakish sense of humor should aid in making the book enjoyable.&rdquo;<br /></em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Publisher&rsquo;s Weekly:</strong> &ldquo;<em>General readers of every stripe will benefit from the author&rsquo;s sophisticated, deeply knowledgeable presentation. If the casual book buyer purchases one science book this year, this should be the one.&rdquo; <br /></em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; New Scientist:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Excitement glows from every page</em>.&rdquo;</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(15, 1, 'Earthborn', '', 0, 1, 14, 24.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Book 5</strong> in the <em>Homecoming series. </em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Humanity&rsquo;s journey from Earth to the stars... a far-future religious saga which manages, brilliantly, to be at once entertaining, unobjectionable, and edifying.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; High above Earth orbits the starship Basilica. On board the huge vessel is a sleeping woman.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Of those who made the journey, Shedemai alone has survived the hundreds of years since the Children of Wetchik returned to Earth. She now wears the Cloak of the Starmaster, and the Oversoul wakes her sometimes to watch over her descendants on the planet below.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The population has grown rapidly&mdash;there are cities and nations now, whole peoples descended from those who followed Nafai or Elemak. But in all the long years of watching and searching, the Oversoul has not found the thing it sought. It has not found the Keeper of the Earth, the central intelligence that also can repair the Oversoul&rsquo;s damaged programming.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The lost Keeper, a sort of planetary consciousness, whose influence is clearly manifest, sets the plot for another struggle between the forces of enlightenment and those of repression and bigotry.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</strong> <em>&ldquo;The plot of the fifth and final volume of Card&rsquo;s Homecoming Series may be a disappointment to fans who have followed Harmony and the Oversoul since the beginning, but this reading is far from a letdown.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "Stefan Rudnicki </em><em>is a master narrator, and nothing &mdash; not complicated names, not departures from the feel of the original four books &mdash; diminishes that talent a whit...<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "Rudnicki&rsquo;s clear, resonant voice bestows an almost-reverent quality to the text, a characteristic that works well with the book&rsquo;s spiritual underpinnings.&rdquo;</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Booklist:</strong> <em>&ldquo;The complex situation, abetted by Card</em><strong>&rsquo;</strong><em>s superior characterization, offers more than enough conflict and questing to keep the yarn moving. The grand saga of human evolution is a demanding category of Science Fiction and fantasy, but Card<strong> </strong>has met its demands quite successfully.&rdquo;</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(16, 1, 'Escape from Alcatraz', '', 0, 1, 9, 16.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A true crime classic... no fiction could conceive it so inhuman!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The daring escape plan of notable mobster <em>Frank Morris</em> and two accomplices became the basis for the 1999 <em>Clint Eastwood</em> movie, <em>Escape from Alcatraz</em>.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Discover the intriguing and absorbing saga of Alcatraz, whose name is still synonymous with punitive isolation and deprivation, in tortuous proximity to San Francisco, one of the world&rsquo;s favorite cities.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The first Spaniard to discover the island was Juan Manuel de Ayala in 1775, who charted San Francisco Bay and named the 22 acre island "<em>La Isla de los Alcatraces</em>" &ndash; also known as &ldquo;<em>The Rock</em>&rdquo;.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Author <em>J. Campbell Bruce</em> chronicles in spellbinding detail Alcatraz Island&rsquo;s transition from a Spanish fort to the maximum-security penitentiary that housed such infamous inmates such as <em>Al Capone. <br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The book describes 14 daring and ingenious escape attempts from this prison.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;One of the things that kept prisoners in check was the long swim that they faced upon a successful escape. Hypothermia would likely set in quickly during the mile-and-a-half swim, and the occasional shark that swam into the bay might find a swimmer to be a tasty treat.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Currents would also be a problem - they race in and out of the Golden Gate at speeds that sometimes exceed 8 miles per hour, more than twice as fast as the quickest person can swim.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Though authorities claim than no prisoner ever escaped in 29 years, Frank Morris and his men&rsquo;s bodies were never found.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Several people have made the treacherous 1.5 mile swim and survived.&nbsp; Also the TV program <em>Mythbusters</em> investigated the account and concluded that such an escape was plausible.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In the stories of how the inmates passed their time, bootlegging took on a new meaning in Alcatraz when inmates made "pruno" which often included such exotic combinations as milk and gasoline.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In 1963, the last prisoner was escorted off&nbsp; Devil&rsquo;s Island and Alcatraz ceased to be a prison.<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Chicago Tribune:</strong><em> "Much more than a prison chronicle, much more than a tale of escape...."</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Los Angeles Time:</strong><em> "Dramatic...thrilling...remarkable!"</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(17, 1, 'Flash Forward', '', 0, 1, 11, 19.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When we know the <em>future</em>... how does that affect our <em>present</em>?<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The popular <strong>TV Series</strong>, <em><strong>Flashforward</strong></em> was based on this book.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A scientific experiment begins, and as the button is pressed, the unexpected occurs: everyone in the world goes to sleep for a few moments and their consciousness are catapulted more than 20 years into the future.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At the end of those moments, when the world reawakens, all human life is transformed by the event and foreknowledge.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Was that shocking revelation a peek at the real, unalterable future, or was it only one of many possible futures? <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; What happens when a man tries to change it, like the doctor who has 20 years to try to prevent his own murder?<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Publishers Weekly:</strong> <em>&ldquo;This first-rate, philosophical journey, a terrific example of idea-driven Science Fiction."<br /></em><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>Ottowa Citizen:</strong> <em>"The Dean of Canadian Science Fiction". <br /></em><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>New York Times Book Review:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Sawyer</em> <em>is a writer of boundless confidence and bold scientific extrapolation.&rdquo; <br /></em><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>Denver Rocky Mountain News:</strong> <em>"Just about the best Science Fiction writer out there."<br /></em><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>Library Journal:</strong> &ldquo;<em><strong>Sawyer</strong> brings a fresh and startling approach to the familiar theme of time travel in a tale that explores the repercussions of knowing the future.&rdquo;</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(18, 1, 'Ghost', '', 0, 1, 10, 19.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:</strong> <em>Confessions of a Counterterrorism Agent<br /><br /></em>Winner of the <em>AudioFile Earphones Award.<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This behind-the-scenes account of one counterterrorism agent&rsquo;s life and career is riveting.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For decades, Fred Burton was a key figure in international counterterrorism and domestic spycraft.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; As a member of the <em>State Department&rsquo;s Diplomatic Security Service</em> in the mid 1980s, he was on the front lines of America&rsquo;s first campaign against terror.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Now, in this hard-hitting memoir,<em><strong> </strong></em>Burton emerges from the shadows to reveal who he is, what he has accomplished, and the threats that lurk unseen except by an experienced, world-wise few.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Burton writes with the skill of Tom Clancy, but his plot contains the extra dimension of historical accuracy. Weiner has distinct voices for all the author&rsquo;s colleagues, enemies, and informants. Each is so convincing that none sound contrived</em>&hellip;&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Publisher&rsquo;s Weekly:</strong> &ldquo;<em>With spy thriller suspense and the clarity of a police report, Ghost reads like a brewing-storm prequel to the current &lsquo;war on terror.&rsquo;&hellip;Of obvious interest to anyone with an eye on world affairs, Burton&rsquo;s account will capture even the casual counterterrorism fans: the spook can actually write</em>!&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>AudioFile:</strong> &ldquo;In the first five minutes you&rsquo;ll be hooked, knowing you&rsquo;re going to enter the dark world of a former counterintelligence agent.<strong> </strong><em>Tom Weiner&rsquo;s</em> deep voice maximizes the impact of the author&rsquo;s machine-gun present-tense style to create an aura of tension and awareness...&rdquo;</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(19, 1, 'God and Mr. Gomez', '', 0, 1, 7, 22.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The book is based on a true story and the author draws hilarious parallels between the Mexican and US temperaments. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When Jack and Denny Smith decided to build a vacation dream house in Baja, California, they had no idea they were entering a phase of their lives "that would capture the fancy of readers throughout the United States." <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Through a series of strange and whimsical adventures, they would find that building a house takes God... and Mr. Gomez. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The renowned columnist for the Los Angeles Times, Jack, falls in love with Mexico and decides to lease a plot of land in Baja California to build their retirement home. The job is entrusted to an exasperating character called Mr. Gomez. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thus a situation evolves where the Smiths have limited resources for the project, the land&rsquo;s original ownership is in question, the country is full of unsuspected and incomprehensible hazards&hellip; and they don&rsquo;t speak any Spanish! <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fortunately, Gomez was always on hand to provide the solution, and the dream house was finally built. In the process, the Smiths came to accept Mr. Gomez&rsquo;s philosophy that all practical problems can be solved with a little time -- and a little tequila. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The building of the house becomes and exercise of defiance in logic and a gradual acceptance of Mr. Gomez&rsquo; culture and idiosyncrasies as an inevitable rite of passage into exotic land retirement!</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(20, 1, 'Greasing the PiÃ±ata', '', 0, 1, 9, 19.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:</strong><em> A Cape Weathers Investigation <br /><br /></em>Tequila soaked adventure&hellip; fast and funny!&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Miles away from home and nowhere near finding the answers, <em>Private Eye Cape Weathers</em>, manages to steal from the mob, piss off the DEA, alienate the local police, confound a computer genius, and somehow lose the client he&rsquo;s been protecting all along.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Tim Maleeny</em> nails it with this installment of<em><strong> </strong>Cape Weathers&rsquo;</em> adventures. It&rsquo;s an intriguing murder mystery crossed with a fast-paced political thriller.The whole thing is tied together with a witty protagonist and a finely tuned sense of humor.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In <em>Greasing The Pi&ntilde;ata</em>, just as in Mexico: &ldquo;<em>Anything can happen, and most of it does</em>".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A former U.S. Senator disappears shortly after his son goes missing. When the son is found dead at the bottom of a water hazard on a golf course in Mexico, it falls to the Senator&rsquo;s estranged daughter to find out what happened.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Private investigator<em><strong> </strong>Cape Weathers</em> doesn&rsquo;t want the case. He doesn&rsquo;t know the terrain and he doesn&rsquo;t like politicians. But he suspects the daughter won&rsquo;t survive very long if he turns her away.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He doesn&rsquo;t know the half of it!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Cape</em> unravels a conspiracy that leads from boardrooms in New York to places in Mexico never seen on any postcard.&nbsp; When his investigation gets the attention of a Mexican drug cartel,<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Cape</em> asks his deadly companion Sally to watch his back. Sally confronts a killer even more dangerous than she is, someone determined to bury the past along with anyone trying to dig it up.<em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; Greasing The Pi&ntilde;ata</em> is a novel about family, politics, and the devastating effects of tequila on a private detective&rsquo;s investigative abilities.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Armando Dur&aacute;n<strong>&rsquo;s</strong> powerful characterizations of sardonic PI Cape Weathers and his associate, Sally Mei, are believable and compelling....Dur&aacute;n depicts Dobbins&rsquo;s estranged daughter, who hires Weathers, with bittersweet sensitivity. With sardonic humor he portrays the discovery of two mutilated bodies in the alligator pond of a Puerto Vallarta golf course....Exceptionally well done.&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em><strong>Library Journal:</strong> <em>"A cracking good mystery definitely not for the faint of heart but just right for readers who like a gritty crime novel with a labyrinth of plot twists."<br /></em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Don Winslow, Bestselling Author of The Dawn Patrol:</strong> <em>"Maleeny is the kind of writer that makes you want to jump in the passenger seat and go for the ride&mdash;okay, maybe with eyes jammed shut and your hands gripping the arm rest&mdash;but then you want to go again."</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(21, 1, 'Gullibler''s Travels', '', 0, 1, 8, 22.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:</strong> <em>The Adventures of a Bad Taste Tourist <br /><br /></em>Winner of the <em>Benjamin Franklin Literary Award for Humor</em><strong><br /><br /></strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; There are tourists&hellip; and then there are TOURISTS!!!!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For years, British journalist <em>Cash Peters</em> trekked around Europe and America visiting some of the tackiest attractions in the world for his hugely popular public radio series, <em>The Bad Taste Tours</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; But a guy can only take so much!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In <em>Gullible&rsquo;s Travels</em> he sets out to prove that <em>Frequent Miles</em> value for a hard working media professional are not so luring after all, but for his listeners they are certainly worth long stretches of <em>Frequent Roars</em>!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Now, as Peters prepares to leave his travel-reporting days behind forever, he takes us along on some of the more ridiculous journeys and adventures of his career: good-bye, <em>Kansas Barbed Wire Museum</em>; au revoir, <em>Paris sewer system tour</em>; auf wiedersehen, <em>Sound of Music locations tour</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Join Peters on this outrageous behind-the-scenes look at the frustrations of a travel reporter on the road. Marvel at his ongoing battle with PR people and at his fights with men dressed in foam costumes.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Gloat and gloat because you don&rsquo;t have to visit the Museum of Bad Art, the Precious Moments Theme Park, or the Museum of Dirt&mdash;and he does.<strong><br />&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Foreword:</strong> &ldquo;<em>With more than a decade of radio experience, Peters is also the obvious choice to narrate his audiobook. His jubilant and animated English-accented voice cannot help but pull listeners into his adventures</em>.&rdquo;</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(22, 1, 'In Morocco', '', 0, 1, 5, 13.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A classic of travel writing.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; With the sense of daring and adventure which characterized her, <em>Edith Wharton </em>sets out to explore Morocco and its people, traveling by military jeep to Rabat, Moulay Idriss, Fez, and Marrakech, from the Atlantic coast to the high Atlas.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Along the way, she witnessed religious ceremonies and ritual dances, visited the opulent palaces of the Sultan and was admitted to the mysterious world of his harem.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Audio file:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Armchair travelers and history buffs will delight in this recording. Wharton&rsquo;s language alternates between unimpassioned frankness and voluptuous description of Morocco&rsquo;s staggering natural and cultural beauty. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &ldquo;</em>Anna Fields<em> takes her cue from the text, delivering a clipped and assured reading when Wharton discusses conveyance, history and other mundane matters, and an unhurried, even dreamy, reading of </em>Wharton&rsquo;s<em> sensuous and evocative descriptions. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &ldquo;Those who have visited or lived in Morocco will feel immediately transported to familiar sites during these descriptive passages.&rdquo;</em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; KLIATT:</strong> &ldquo;<em>In Morocco is narrated with sensitivity by Fields, who conveys the literary quality of the writing and the exotic quality of the experience.&rdquo;</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(23, 1, 'Invasive Procedures', '', 0, 1, 12, 22.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; What happens when man can play God? ... Frankenstein&rsquo;s dilemma transported by Science Fiction into the future.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> </strong>George Galen<strong> </strong></em>is a brilliant scientist, a pioneer in gene therapy. But Galen is dangerously insane. He has created a method to alter human DNA, not just to heal diseases, but also to &ldquo;improve&rdquo; people: make them stronger, make them able to heal more quickly&hellip;and make them compliant to his will.<em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> Frank Hartman</em> is also a brilliant virologist, working for the government&rsquo;s ultra-secret biohazard agency. He has discovered how to neutralize Galen&rsquo;s DNA-changing virus.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Now he is the one man who stands in the way of Galen&rsquo;s plan to "improve" the entire human race.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp; Publishers Weekly:</strong> <em>&ldquo;An intriguing medical thriller&hellip;raises pertinent regulatory questions.&rdquo;</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Booklist:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Wins the reader over on the basis of execution&hellip;with pace, characterization, and chilling suspense all polished to a high gloss.&rdquo;</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
