(156, 2, 'Libranos del mal', '', 0, 2, 6, 24.99, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Esta obra revela los detalles, en primera persona, del&nbsp; secuestro deErnestina Sodi en M&eacute;xico.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Uno de los secuestros que mayor consternaci&oacute;n ha causado en la opini&oacute;n p&uacute;blica mexicana fue el de la escritora Ernestina Sodi y su hermana, la actriz Laura Zapata, perpetrado por la banda de secuestradores "<em>Los Tiras</em>", quienes se encuentran tras las rejas a ra&iacute;z de la denuncia que ambas presentaron despu&eacute;s de su liberaci&oacute;n. &nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Con los ojos vendados gran parte de su captura, Ernestina aprende, por sus voces y olores, a reconocer los miembros de esta pandilla muy bien organizada de brutales secuestradores.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sometida a martirios f&iacute;sicos y psicol&oacute;gicos, Ernestina se vale de su ingenio para hacerse amiga de los pandilleros en cuyas manos estaba su vida.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En una versi&oacute;n invertida del s&iacute;ndrome de Estocolmo, uno de los secuestradores se enamora de la v&iacute;ctima y le lleva flores, incluso contrata una banda de mariachis para que le canten.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vali&eacute;ndose de una escritura &iacute;ntima y serena, la autora muestra su experiencia a trav&eacute;s de una l&iacute;nea fr&aacute;gil que separa la cordura de la demencia, la vida de la muerte. Somos testigos, adem&aacute;s, de su reconstrucci&oacute;n an&iacute;mica y corporal que comienza penosa, lenta, pero plena.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; El recuento lleva a las profundidades de la mentalidad del criminal, su furia y su violencia.&nbsp; Los acontecimientos desencadenan en un desenlace que no resulta f&aacute;cil de olvidar para la autora, ni su audiencia.</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(157, 2, 'Lo que llamamos muerte', '', 0, 2, 14, 29.99, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subt&iacute;tulo:</strong><em> El antes y el despu&eacute;s</em><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Esta es una obra autobiogr&aacute;fica en la que la autora analiza principios sobre la experiencia de muerte y duelo entre las personas bas&aacute;ndose en su&nbsp; experiencia profesional y personal, acompa&ntilde;ando personas en el proceso de muerte y duelo. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; La muerte encierra un proceso de transformaci&oacute;n radical. Para poder entender su antes y su despu&eacute;s, la autora utiliza como hilo argumental un hecho real: el fallecimiento inesperado de un joven al que sus hijos estaban unidos por fuertes lazos afectivos, y el "viaje" que comienza para las personas "que se quedan".<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cuando se sufre la p&eacute;rdida de un ser querido, la mayor&iacute;a de las personas no saben c&oacute;mo canalizar sus emociones y en su desolaci&oacute;n encuentran que no saben c&oacute;mo habr&aacute;n de seguir viviendo.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En un an&aacute;lisis de las eternas preguntas: &iquest;C&oacute;mo sanar la culpa? &iquest;C&oacute;mo hacer frente al dolor emocional? &iquest;Hay algo m&aacute;s all&aacute; de la muerte?... la obra busca llevar a su audiencia a profundizar sus sentimientos para revelarnos otra perspectiva de la muerte.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Es una herramienta terapeutica, espiritual y transpersonal para enfrentar la muerte a trav&eacute;s de una nueva conciencia de amor por la vida y vivir en el ahora como un presente sin fin. &nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Esas son sus conclusiones como profesional en el campo de lo que hoy se llama tanatolog&iacute;a, pedagog&iacute;a de la muerte, cuidados paliativos o, lo que ella llama, &ldquo;<em>el acompa&ntilde;amiento a personas en los procesos de muerte y de duelo</em>&rdquo;.</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(158, 2, 'Los cinco nudos', '', 0, 2, 8, 24.99, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cinco personas&hellip;<em>un maestro, un sacerdote, el Presidente de un banco, una estudiante universitaria y un artista</em>... quedan atrapadas en un ascensor durante varias horas. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No hay espacio suficiente. El calor es sofocante. La ansiedad va transform&aacute;ndose en p&aacute;nico. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Esos personajes, aparentemente tan diferentes, comparten y provocan unos en otros reacciones durante su encierro que los lleva a imaginar que las cosas m&aacute;s insignificantes son realmente desproporcionados problemas y pesadillas.&nbsp; Este ejercicio psicol&oacute;gico los lleva a sacar de lo m&aacute;s profundos de sus psiquis recuerdos enterrados y deseos frustrados.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sus vidas despu&eacute;s de la experiencia quedar&aacute;n enmara&ntilde;adas en nudos inquebrantables.&nbsp; En vez de cap&iacute;tulos el libro est&aacute; dividido en las horas de encierro, cada una m&aacute;s intensa y atrapante que la anterior.</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(159, 2, 'Los nuevos sofistas', '', 0, 2, 8, 24.99, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &iquest;Est&aacute; la salvaci&oacute;n del hombre en su capacidad de abrirse a sus dict&aacute;menes internos para volver a encontrar la humanidad que ha perdido a los l&iacute;mites e ineficiencias de los sistemas pol&iacute;ticos y sociales de nuestros tiempos? &nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pero, &iquest;estamos todavia a tiempo de cambiar el derrotero del la humanidad hacia su fin?<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En <em>&ldquo;Los nuevos sofistas&rdquo; </em>el reconocido autor cubano Juan Jacobo-Doger,&nbsp; abre de nuevo la puerta del misterioso mundo de la mente humana.&nbsp; En esta ocasi&oacute;n para denunciar y traer a la luz la ineficacia fulminantes de los sistemas pol&iacute;ticos y la desesperanza que el status quo representa para la sociedad actual.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Necesitados de los heraldos de la denuncia, los entes comprometidos se convierten en la mejor arma contra la desidia y la ignorancia. Mientras que los valores y la moral personal se proyectan como el puente de salvaci&oacute;n.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &iquest;Puede el hombre moderno regresar a sus ra&iacute;ces, humaniz&aacute;ndose de nuevo, o ya un dictamen divino ha creado el veredicto final?</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(160, 2, 'Los pueblos indios de Mexico hoy', '', 0, 2, 5, 24.99, 0, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Derrotados por la conquista, &ldquo;evangelizados&rdquo; y sometidos al vasallaje de la corona espa&ntilde;ola durante tres siglos, declarados &ldquo;inexistentes&rdquo; por el liberalismo decimon&oacute;nico, despojados de sus tierras comunales por lo que se vuelven agraristas en la revoluci&oacute;n de 1910, y oprimidos por el paternalismo indigenista contempor&aacute;neo al despuntar el siglo XXI, &iquest;qu&eacute; son hoy los pueblos indios de M&eacute;xico? <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; El descubrimiento y comprensi&oacute;n de la existencia del<em> Nuevo Mundo </em>exigi&oacute; de una re-definici&oacute;n de&nbsp; muchos aspectos religiosos y pol&iacute;ticos en el <em>Viejo Mundo</em><strong> </strong>del siglo XV.<br /><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Carlos Montemayor </em>analiza el complejo proceso de invenci&oacute;n y formulaci&oacute;n de ideas contradictorias sobre los pueblos ind&iacute;genas que se ha dado desde la conquista hasta nuestros d&iacute;as, tanto en Europa como en M&eacute;xico... y que tienen como eje la resistencia al dominio de la corona espa&ntilde;ola y del estado mexicano. <br /><br /><strong>Observa el autor que:</strong> <em>&ldquo;En aquel presente complejo era necesario crear otra imagen del mundo, inventar un nuevo espacio geogr&aacute;fico y pol&iacute;tico que modificar&iacute;a los conceptos mismos de humanidad. La nueva geograf&iacute;a del mundo iba m&aacute;s all&aacute; de las jornadas de navegaci&oacute;n y de las ediciones de cart&oacute;grafos&hellip;<br />&ldquo;El proceso no fue breve ni sencillo. En un momento, Am&eacute;rica era un inmenso territorio apropiable y explotable. En otro, era la revelaci&oacute;n m&aacute;s importante que la humanidad hab&iacute;a recibido de la Divina Providencia.&rdquo;</em><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Esas distintas interpretaciones de lo que significaba el<em> Nuevo Mundo </em>forjaron a su vez la manera en que se lidi&oacute; con los nuevos territorios y sus habitantes.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dentro de ese contexto, Montemayor ofrece un an&aacute;lisis de la compleja trayectoria del pueblo ind&iacute;gena mexicano desde la conquista hasta nuestros d&iacute;as.</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(161, 2, 'Los que falsificaron la firma de Dios', '', 0, 2, 11, 29.99, 1, '', '<p><strong>Premio Nacional de la Novela en la Rep&uacute;blica Dominicana</strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tambi&eacute;n fue el Bestseller m&aacute;s vendido en la Rep&uacute;blica Dominicana y similar recepci&oacute;n por toda Am&eacute;rica Latina, lo que llev&oacute; a que fuera traducido y editado tambi&eacute;n por una editorial estadounidense.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cuando se public&oacute; esta novela provoc&oacute; de inmediato la ira del entonces Presidente Joaqu&iacute;n Balaguer, protagonista aleg&oacute;rico de la obra; y de otros personajes que se vieron retratados en las p&aacute;ginas de una historia en la que result&oacute; inevitable que la ficci&oacute;n se identificara con&nbsp; la cruda realidad del poder de los caudillos Trujillo y Balaguer.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tanto asi que se negaron a que se le hiciera entrega del Premio Nacional conferido... lo que ayud&oacute; a propiciar la fama de la que goza la obra.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; La historia muestra las peripecias de tres estudiantes seminaristas que tratan de alcanzar sus ideales en la vida escapando de las restricciones del catolicismo para entrar al medio de una sociedad brutal marcada por la represi&oacute;n e inestabilidad pol&iacute;tica. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Contrario a otros autores latinoamericanos que se expresan en contra de gobiernos dictatoriales,&nbsp; Senci&oacute;n lo hizo mientras todav&iacute;a viv&iacute;a en la Rep&uacute;blica Dominicana, por lo que en muchas ocasiones se vio amenazado de muerte.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Es una desafiante novela para los hombres y mujeres libres porque engendra en ellos temor contra los que atentan contra los derechos y libertades de los protagonistas.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; El &eacute;xito de la novela de Senci&oacute;n, no fue un efecto de marketing sino una clara expresi&oacute;n que los destructivos enmara&ntilde;amientos de la religi&oacute;n, la pol&iacute;tica y el sexo que ofrece la obra, se encuentran tambi&eacute;n en muchas otras partes del globo.</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(162, 2, 'Manual para el exito familiar', '', 0, 2, 5, 24.99, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sorprende que una actividad tan trascendental como formar y conservar una familia sea emprendida sin ninguna preparaci&oacute;n ni conocimiento y que, peor a&uacute;n,&nbsp; est&eacute; rodeada de un c&uacute;mulo de mitos, ideas err&oacute;neas y prejuicios transmitidos a trav&eacute;s de las generaciones. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; El principio de esta confusi&oacute;n es creer que nacemos con una programaci&oacute;n gen&eacute;tica para llevarla a cabo. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Otro malentendido es suponer que no existen salidas ante las crisis familiares o que est&aacute;n fuera de nuestro alcance. <br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En esta obra se analiza c&oacute;mo manejar los aspectos conflictivos de: <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull; la pareja <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull; la sexualidad <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull; la familia pol&iacute;tica <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull; la infidelidad <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull; las adicciones <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull; el dinero <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull; la educaci&oacute;n de los hijos <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull; la violencia intrafamiliar <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull; el divorcio&nbsp; y el duelo<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lizi Rodr&iacute;guez, a partir de una amplia experiencia profesional, afirma que el &eacute;xito familiar debe ser un estilo de vida y gozarse a plenitud. Aprender a reconocer cu&aacute;les son los problemas m&aacute;s comunes y saber c&oacute;mo afrontarlos es el primer paso hacia su soluci&oacute;n.</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(163, 1, '2666', '', 0, 1, 40, 44.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Best Book of the Year </strong>by the <em>New York Times, Los Angeles Times, San Fr</em><em>ancisco Chronicle, Seattle Times, New York magazine </em>and <em>Time magazine</em>.<strong><br />National Book Critics Award<br /></strong><strong>Best of the Month</strong> --<em>Amazon</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This is one of the spectacular audio productions of major works in our time.<strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Roberto Bola&ntilde;o&rsquo;s surrealist Magnum Opus, set in Europe and South America, is divided into five books, each read here by a different Narrator, each in his way extraordinary."</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Grandiose exploration of parallel lives, secret histories, violence, death, serial killings, real life dramas and invention... but also, so much more!The last novel written by Chilean-born novelist Roberto Bola&ntilde;o depicting the unsolved and ongoing serial murders of Ciudad Ju&aacute;rez (Santa Teresa in the novel).<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; These are the same events that inspired the movie <strong>Bordertown</strong> with <em><strong>Jennifer Lopez, Antonio Banderas</strong> </em>and <em><strong>Martin Sheen</strong></em>.<em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp; 2666</strong><strong> </strong></em>was greeted across Europe and Latin America as Bola&ntilde;o&rsquo;s highest achievement, surpassing even his previous work in its strangeness, beauty, and scope.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Its throng of unforgettable characters includes academics and convicts, an American sportswriter, an elusive German novelist, and a teenage student and her widowed, mentally unstable father.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Their lives intersect in the urban sprawl of Santa Teresa&mdash;a fictional Ciudad Ju&aacute;rez&mdash;on the U.S.-Mexico border, where hundreds of young factory workers in the novel, as in real life, have disappeared.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The novel is really a compendium of five parts, initially meant by Bola&ntilde;o to be a series of sequels:&nbsp; <em><strong>The Part of the Critics; The Part of Amalfitano; The Part of Fate; The Part of Crimes</strong>;</em> and <em>The <strong>Part of Archimboldi</strong> </em>- all linked by varying degrees of concern with the unsolved murders.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial Times:</strong> "<em>As before, Bola&ntilde;o is preoccupied with parallel lives and secret histories. Largely written after 9/11, the novel manifests a new emphasis on the dangerousness of the modern world...<strong>2666 </strong>is an excruciatingly challenging novel, in which Bola&ntilde;o redraws the boundaries of fiction. <br />&ldquo;It is bold in a way that few works really are &ndash; it kicks away the divide between playfulness and seriousness. And it reminds us that literature at its best inhabits what Bola&ntilde;o, with a customary wink at his own pomposity, called "the territory of risk" &ndash; it takes us to places we might not wish to go."</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; El Pa&iacute;s:</strong> <em>&ldquo;One of those strange, exquisite, and astonishing experiences that literature offers us only once in a very long time&hellip;.a writer in full pursuit of the Total Novel, one that not only completes his life&rsquo;s work but redefines it and raises it to new dizzying heights.&rdquo;</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Washington Post:</strong> <em>&ldquo;The <strong>Gabriel Garc&iacute;a M&aacute;rquez</strong> of our time: politically engaged, formally daring and wildly imaginative....[<strong>2666</strong>] should cement his reputation as a world-class novelist&hellip;.[Bola&ntilde;o] exults in his indefatigable storytelling skills and his mastery of an arsenal of styles With <strong>2666</strong>, Bola&ntilde;o joins the ambitious overachievers of the 20th-century novel, those like<strong> Proust, Musil, Joyce, Gaddis, Pynchon, Fuentes</strong> and <strong>Vollmann</strong>, who push the novel far past its conventional size and scope to encompass an entire era, deploying encyclopedic knowledge and stylistic verve to offer a grand, if sometimes idiosyncratic summation of their culture and the novelist&rsquo;s place in it. Bola&ntilde;o has joined the immortals.&rdquo;</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Amazon.com Review:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Bolano&rsquo;s true masterpiece....he writes with a horror that is both haunting and deeply humane.&rdquo;</em><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Listen to Bola&ntilde;o&rsquo;s first novel, <em><strong>The Savage Detectives </strong></em>here<strong> www.MundoHablado.com</strong></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(165, 1, 'American Gangster', '', 0, 2, 10, 19.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This vivid journalistic expose was the basis for the Universal  Pictures&rsquo; release, <em>American Gangster</em>, starring Denzel Washington  and <em>Russell Crowe.</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No one ever paid much attention to  Frank Lucas, the quiet limo driver of one of the Black mobsters in New  York. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; But when his boss meets an unexpected death, Frank takes  the chance to fill the vacuum in the underground power structure to  build his own empire and realize his own version of the American Dream.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Thanks to his innate leadership qualities and a ruthless operational  ethic, he takes control of the drug traffic in the Big Apple flooding  the streets with higher quality/lower priced heroin smuggled from the  East in the coffins of dead soldiers from Vietnam. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the  1970s, Frank Lucas was the king of the Harlem drug trade, bringing in  over a million dollars a day. He lived a glamorous life, hobnobbing with  athletes, musicians, and politicians, but Lucas was a ruthless  gangster. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In <em>American Gangster</em>, Mark Jacobson&rsquo;s  captivating account of the life of Frank Lucas joins other tales of New  York City from the past thirty years. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The collection features a  number of Jacobson&rsquo;s most famous essays, as well as previously  unpublished works and more recent articles. Together, they create a  vibrant, many-layered portrait of the most fascinating city in the  world, by one of the most acclaimed journalists of our time.</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(166, 1, 'Blood Diamonds', '', 0, 2, 7, 20.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:</strong> <em>Tracing the Deadly Path of the World&rsquo;s Most Precious  Stones<br /><br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The 2006 movie <em>Blood Diamonds</em> with <em>Leonardo  DiCaprio</em> and <em>Jennifer Connelly</em>, was based on this book.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Discover the international diamond trail of brutality, horror and  profit... a story of global consequences! <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A &ldquo;<em>conflict  diamond</em>&rdquo; is one that is mined illegally by groups trying to  overthrow the legitimate governments of certain countries. The profits  from these stolen mines are used to continue funding for their brutal,  murderous military actions.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This is one of these gripping  stories of blood diamonds by Greg Campbell.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the 90s, the  country of Sierra Leone was under terrible civil war between the  legitimate government and the Revolutionary United Front (RUF) a group  that had no real ideology other than takeover of the government, money,  and according to Campbell, the diamond fields of the country. They did  so in a horribly violent way.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Award-winning journalist Greg  Campbell traces the deadly trail of these diamonds and the repercussions  felt far beyond the poor and war-ridden country of Sierra Leone.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp; New York Times:</strong> &ldquo;Mr. Campbell tells this complex tale  from a personal, feet-on-the ground perspective....He reminds us that  there is no longer any such thing as an isolated conflict that  governments and corporations can ignore with impunity.&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Washington  Times:</strong> &ldquo;A vivid, hair-raising tale of brutal proportions that  outdistances any fictional tale of derring-do.&rdquo; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>AudioFile: </strong>&ldquo;Though  he steps into the vocal cadence of African leaders, Tom Weiner wisely  doesn&rsquo;t overdramatize. His pace, clarity, and compelling tone work to  keep listener attention throughout a detailed explanation of how the  diamond market works."</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(167, 1, 'Che Guevara', '', 0, 2, 37, 44.95, 1, '', '<p><strong><span lang="EN-US">Subtitle:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"> <em>A  Revolutionary Life</em> <br /><br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This  acclaimed US bestseller chronicles the life of the dashing rebel from  Argentina, Che Guevara, whose epic dream was to end poverty and  injustice in the third world through armed revolution.</span><span lang="EN-US"><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; From his comfortable Argentine upbringing to the  battlefields of the Cuban revolution, from the halls of power in  Castro&rsquo;s government to his failures in the Congo and ultimately his  assassination in the Bolivian jungle.</span><span lang="EN-US"><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Through exclusive access to previously unavailable personal archives,  government documents and rare interviews, the author reveals many  aspects of Che&rsquo;s life long cloaked in secrecy and intrigue. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"> <em>&ldquo;Excellent....admirably  honest staggeringly researched....It is unlikely that after Anderson&rsquo;s  exhaustive contribution, much more will be learned about Guevara.&rdquo;</em></span><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  <strong><span lang="EN-US">Los Angeles</span></strong><strong><span lang="EN-US"> Times:</span></strong><em><span lang="EN-US"> &ldquo;An enduring achievement. It is  hard to imagine that any will match the volume and detail of the  research here.... victories and failures, equally spectacular, are part  of our common history&hellip;.Che lives, not only in this book, but in the  world.&rdquo;</span></em><strong><span lang="EN-US"><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; New York Times Book  Review:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"> <em>&ldquo;A sweeping biography of the  Latino revolutionary and pop-culture hero....Anderson paints a portrait  of Guevara as both hero and fanatic....Students of Che&rsquo;s life and deeds  need look no farther than Anderson&rsquo;s volume.&rdquo;</em></span><strong><span lang="EN-US"><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Boston Globe:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"> <em>&ldquo;  exceptional and exciting biography....Anderson&rsquo;s up-close look, with  beauty marks and tragic flaws so effortlessly rendered, brings the  reader face to face with a man whose &rsquo;unshakable faith in his beliefs  was made more powerful by his unusual combination of romantic passion  and a coldly analytical mind.&rsquo;...an invaluable addition to the  literature of American revolutionaries.&rdquo;</em></span></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(168, 2, 'Mi vida saxual', '', 0, 2, 12, 24.99, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Esta es una picaresca autobiograf&iacute;a del saxofonista y clarinetista m&aacute;s destacado del jazz latino en que examina dimensiones poco conocidas de su trayectoria art&iacute;stica<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Es un libro de memorias pero no a partir del cansancio de una vida hecha, sino el recuento de las vivencias m&aacute;s importantes de un hombre en plena exaltaci&oacute;n de su carrera art&iacute;stica; un alto en el camino para colocar las experiencias en su sitio, y compartirlas con amigos-admiradores-lectores, y es tambi&eacute;n una declaraci&oacute;n de principios ante los dem&aacute;s&hellip; ante la historia. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "<em>El virtuoso del saxof&oacute;n</em>" no solo es el arquetipo del m&uacute;sico cubano, sino tambi&eacute;n el ser humano que ha tratado de ser fiel a si mismo en el marasmo de la historia que le toco vivir.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Escribiendo y narrando su &ldquo;vida saxual&rdquo; el legendario compositor y m&uacute;sico cubano muestra su pasi&oacute;n art&iacute;stica y social al hablar de todo, desde la importancia de aprender a leer m&uacute;sica de ni&ntilde;o bajo el tutelaje de padre, tambi&eacute;n saxofonista profesional, a comentar sobre las opiniones del chelista Yo-Yo Ma sobre el comunismo, a detalles de su propia historia como exiliado de un gobierno que restring&iacute;a la expresi&oacute;n art&iacute;stica seg&uacute;n los vol&aacute;tiles dict&aacute;menes de su caudillo. &nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; El relato es &aacute;gil y sobre todo humor&iacute;stico, que va y viene entre detalles de su vida como sus relaciones profesionales y personales con gigantes como Celia Cruz, Tito Puentes, Dizzie Gillespie, y un sin&uacute;mero de otros sobre los cuales cuenta los episodios que los unieron en la m&uacute;sica y en su vida privada. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Mi vida saxual</em> est&aacute; escrito con un estilo ameno, humor&iacute;stico, &aacute;gil, lleno de an&eacute;cdotas y opiniones personales, es la cr&oacute;nica de una &eacute;poca, de una ciudad, de una generaci&oacute;n.</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(169, 1, 'Flash Forward', '', 0, 2, 11, 19.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp; When we know the <em>future</em>... how does that affect our <em>present</em>?<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  The popular TV Series, <em>Flashforward</em> was based on  this book.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A scientific experiment begins, and as the button is  pressed, the unexpected occurs: everyone in the world goes to sleep for a  few moments and their consciousness are catapulted more than 20 years  into the future.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At the end of those moments, when the world  reawakens, all human life is transformed by the event and foreknowledge.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Was that shocking revelation a peek at the real, unalterable future, or  was it only one of many possible futures? <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; What happens when a  man tries to change it, like the doctor who has 20 years to try to  prevent his own murder?<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Publishers Weekly:</strong> <em>&ldquo;This  first-rate, philosophical journey, a terrific example of idea-driven  Science Fiction."<br /></em><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>Ottowa Citizen:</strong> <em>"The Dean  of Canadian Science Fiction". <br /></em><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>New York Times  Book Review:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Sawyer</em> <em>is a writer of boundless confidence  and bold scientific extrapolation.&rdquo; <br /></em><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>Denver Rocky  Mountain News:</strong> <em>"Just about the best Science Fiction writer out  there."<br /></em><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>Library Journal:</strong> &ldquo;<em><strong>Sawyer</strong> brings a fresh and startling approach to the familiar theme of time  travel in a tale that explores the repercussions of knowing the future.&rdquo;</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(170, 1, 'God and Mr. Gomez', '', 0, 2, 7, 22.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The book is based on a true story and the author draws hilarious  parallels between the Mexican and US temperaments. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When Jack  and Denny Smith decided to build a vacation dream house in Baja,  California, they had no idea they were entering a phase of their lives  "that would capture the fancy of readers throughout the United States." <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Through a series of strange and whimsical adventures, they would find  that building a house takes God... and Mr. Gomez. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The renowned  columnist for the Los Angeles Times, Jack, falls in love with Mexico and  decides to lease a plot of land in Baja California to build their  retirement home. The job is entrusted to an exasperating character  called Mr. Gomez. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thus a situation evolves where the Smiths  have limited resources for the project, the land&rsquo;s original ownership is  in question, the country is full of unsuspected and incomprehensible  hazards&hellip; and they don&rsquo;t speak any Spanish! <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fortunately, Gomez  was always on hand to provide the solution, and the dream house was  finally built. In the process, the Smiths came to accept Mr. Gomez&rsquo;s  philosophy that all practical problems can be solved with a little time  -- and a little tequila. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The building of the house becomes and  exercise of defiance in logic and a gradual acceptance of Mr. Gomez&rsquo;  culture and idiosyncrasies as an inevitable rite of passage into exotic  land retirement!</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(171, 1, 'Greasing the PiÃ±ata', '', 0, 2, 9, 22.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Subtitle:</strong><em> A Cape Weathers Investigation <br /><br /></em>Tequila  soaked adventure&hellip; fast and funny!&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Miles away from home  and nowhere near finding the answers, <em>Private Eye Cape Weathers</em>,  manages to steal from the mob, piss off the DEA, alienate the local  police, confound a computer genius, and somehow lose the client he&rsquo;s  been protecting all along.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Tim Maleeny</em> nails it with this  installment of<em><strong> </strong>Cape Weathers&rsquo;</em> adventures. It&rsquo;s an  intriguing murder mystery crossed with a fast-paced political  thriller.The whole thing is tied together with a witty protagonist and a  finely tuned sense of humor.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In <em>Greasing The Pi&ntilde;ata</em>,  just as in Mexico: &ldquo;<em>Anything can happen, and most of it does</em>".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  A former U.S. Senator disappears shortly after his son goes missing.  When the son is found dead at the bottom of a water hazard on a golf  course in Mexico, it falls to the Senator&rsquo;s estranged daughter to find  out what happened.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Private investigator<em><strong> </strong>Cape Weathers</em> doesn&rsquo;t want the case. He doesn&rsquo;t know the terrain and he doesn&rsquo;t like  politicians. But he suspects the daughter won&rsquo;t survive very long if he  turns her away.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He doesn&rsquo;t know the half of it!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Cape</em> unravels a conspiracy that leads from boardrooms in New York to places  in Mexico never seen on any postcard.&nbsp; When his investigation gets the  attention of a Mexican drug cartel,<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Cape</em> asks his deadly  companion Sally to watch his back. Sally confronts a killer even more  dangerous than she is, someone determined to bury the past along with  anyone trying to dig it up.<em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; Greasing The Pi&ntilde;ata</em> is  a novel about family, politics, and the devastating effects of tequila  on a private detective&rsquo;s investigative abilities.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  AudioFile:</strong> &ldquo;<em>Armando Dur&aacute;n<strong>&rsquo;s</strong> powerful characterizations of  sardonic PI Cape Weathers and his associate, Sally Mei, are believable  and compelling....Dur&aacute;n depicts Dobbins&rsquo;s estranged daughter, who hires  Weathers, with bittersweet sensitivity. With sardonic humor he portrays  the discovery of two mutilated bodies in the alligator pond of a Puerto  Vallarta golf course....Exceptionally well done.&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em><strong>Library  Journal:</strong> <em>"A cracking good mystery definitely not for the faint  of heart but just right for readers who like a gritty crime novel with a  labyrinth of plot twists."<br /></em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Don Winslow, Bestselling  Author of The Dawn Patrol:</strong> <em>"Maleeny is the kind of writer that  makes you want to jump in the passenger seat and go for the ride&mdash;okay,  maybe with eyes jammed shut and your hands gripping the arm rest&mdash;but  then you want to go again."</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(172, 1, 'The Fall of Che Guevara', '', 0, 2, 6, 22.95, 1, '', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; How much was the US and the CIA got involved in the execution of Che in  Bolivia?<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This book tells the dramatic story of the United  States government&rsquo;s response to Guevara&rsquo;s ill-starred insurgency in  Bolivia in 1967.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Historian Henry Butterfield Ryan argues that  Guevara&rsquo;s life must be re-evaluated in light of secret documents  released by the CIA, the State Department, the Pentagon and the National  Security Council.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This dramatic account of the last days of Che  Guevara is sure to appeal to scholars and students of United States  foreign policy, Latin American history, military history, and to all  others interested in this modern revolutionary&rsquo;s remarkable life.<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  <strong>Miami Herald:</strong> "<em>As a behind-the-scenes look into the issues  and personalities that shaped U.S. foreign policy for Latin America...  is fascinating.&rdquo;<br /></em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Journal of Military History:</strong> "Th<em>is  work is well researched, utilizing Cuban, U.S., and Bolivian sources,  and is a cracking good read</em>."<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Washington Monthly:</strong> "<em>Ryan  offers a thoughtful critique of both the operational and  intelligence-gathering aspects of the U.S. intervention against the  Cuban intervention in Bolivia... He enlivens his narrative with vivid  portraits of the two American officials who played key parts in the hunt  for Guevara... This is a welcome addition to the literature on both Che  Guevara and U.S. intervention in Latin America</em>."</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(173, 1, 'The Prestige', '', 0, 2, 13, 22.95, 1, '', '<p>Winner of <strong>AudioFile Earphones Award and the World Fantasy Award</strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Hugh Jackman, Michael Caine, Christian Bale and David Bowie starred in  the latest movie adaptation of <em>The Prestige.<br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>&nbsp; The  Prestige</em> is one of Priest&rsquo;s most acclaimed novels, being winner of  both the <em>World Fantasy Award </em>and the J<em>ames Tait Black Memorial  Prize for Fiction.</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In 1878, two  young stage magicians clash in the dark during the course of a  fraudulent s&eacute;ance. From this moment on, their lives become webs of  deceit and revelation as they vie to outwit and expose each other. Their  rivalry will take them to the peaks of their careers&mdash;but with terrible  consequences.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the course of pursuing each other&rsquo;s ruin, they  will deploy all the deception their magician&rsquo;s craft can command, the  highest misdirection and the darkest science. Blood will be spilled, but  it will not be enough. In the end, their legacy will pass on for  generations to descendants who must, for their sanity&rsquo;s sake, untangle  their puzzle.<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</strong> "<em>Priest&rsquo;s remarkable  novel has been produced as an audiobook every bit as  remarkable....Hearing Vance mellifluously pronounce words like  &lsquo;prestidigitator&rsquo; as if they were part of his normal speech makes the  book worth the time, but there is so much more....Vance expertly  portrays these two men as their lives (and their tricks) are slowly  revealed</em>."<strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SFFAudio.com:</strong> "<em>It&rsquo;s difficult to say  how long it&rsquo;s been since I&rsquo;ve been so enthralled with an audiobook....  performance was stellar. Because of his subtle care, the surprises of  the novel were enhanced....The result is an intricate web that is slowly  unraveled throughout the book. It&rsquo;s an audiobook that merits a second  listen</em>."</p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(174, 1, 'The Savage Detectives', '', 0, 2, 27, 34.95, 1, '', '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Savage Detectives</em> is an exuberant, wildly inventive and  ambitious novel from one of the greatest Latin American authors of our  age. The late Chilean writer Roberto Bola&ntilde;o has been called the Garc&iacute;a  Marquez of his generation.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In this dazzling novel, the book that  established his international reputation, Bola&ntilde;o tells the story of two  modern-day Quixotes &mdash; the last survivors of an underground literary  movement, perhaps of literature itself &mdash; on a tragicomic quest through a  darkening, entropic universe.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Brilliantly rendered into English  by Natasha Wimmer, the acclaimed translator of Bola&ntilde;o&rsquo;s other great  masterwork,<em> 2666</em>. (also available here at <strong>www.MundoHablado.com</strong>)<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  <strong>New York Times:</strong> <em>"Wildly enjoyable....Bola&ntilde;o beautifully  manages to keep his comedy and his pathos in the same family."<br /></em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Publishers Weekly:</strong> <em>"This novel will allow English speaking  readers to discover a truly great writer... There are copious, and  acidly hilarious, references to the Latin American literary scene, and  one needn&rsquo;t be an insider to get the jokes... Bola&ntilde;o fashions an  engrossing lost world of youth and utopian ambition, as particular and  vivid as it is sad and uncontainable."<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em><strong>Bookmarks  Magazine:</strong> <em>"By turns humorous and sad, this literary mystery also  affirms the value of literature and serves as a modern history of the  Latin American literary scene... inventive and entertaining."<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em><strong>Vogue:</strong> <em>"Roberto Bola&ntilde;o&rsquo;s masterwork...confirms this Chilean&rsquo;s status as  Latin America&rsquo;s literary enfant terrible."</em><br /><br />You can also  listen to Bola&ntilde;o&rsquo;s posthumous work, <em><strong>2666</strong></em>, here at <strong>www.MundoHablado.com</strong></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(175, 1, 'Atlas Shrugged', '', 0, 2, 63, 49.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>4th Most Downloaded Adult Fiction Audiobook from Libraries</strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  A Hollywood re-make of this movie about the rise and fall of the railroad industry,  based on this book, was just released in 2011.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; What if all the  genius and leaders of innovation and progress went on strike?<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In  defense of those greatest of human qualities that have made  civilization possible, one man sets out to show what would happen to the  world if all the heroes of innovation and industry went on strike.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Exemplified by the fall of the railroad industry, once a giant in the  country,<em><strong> </strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Atlas Shrugged</em> denounces about the  dangers of too much government intervention that can lead to many of the  very financial crisis the country is experiencing today. <strong><em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></strong>&nbsp;  Atlas Shrugged is a compelling mystery, but it is also a story with a  profound and original philosophy that provides answers to the problems  we&rsquo;re facing in our world right now.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Many people feel inspired  after reading the novel, and that is a major reason why the book is  still in such high demand.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tremendous in scope and breathtaking  in its suspense, <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Atlas Shrugged</em> is Ayn Rand&rsquo;s Magnum  Opus, an electrifying moral defense of capitalism and free enterprise --  a defense that had an electrifying effect on millions of readers&mdash;and  now listeners&mdash;who had never heard capitalism defended in other than  technical terms.<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>New York Herald Tribune:</strong> "A vibrant  and powerful novel of ideas."<strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; New York Daily Mirror:</strong> <em>"Ayn  Rand is destined to rank in history as the outstanding novelist and  most profound philosopher of the twentieth century."</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  AudioFile:</strong> <em>"Narrator Scott Brick </em><em>takes listeners on a  journey so extraordinary they&rsquo;ll hardly notice the book&rsquo;s length. While  his performance offers little in the way of theatrics, Brick is capable  of garnering sympathy and, perhaps most importantly, devout attention  for Rand&rsquo;s plot and characters. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "On the surface, Brick&rsquo;s voice  is a cool, unrelenting force determined to capture every facet of Rand&rsquo;</em><em>s  complex story. But amid his calm and collected delivery, he taps into a  more colorful emotional palette that will keep listeners involved.  Brick</em><em><strong>&rsquo;</strong>s subtle delivery holds far more than meets the  ear."</em></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(176, 1, '2666', '', 0, 2, 40, 44.95, 1, '', '<p><strong>Best Book of the Year </strong>by the <em>New York Times, Los Angeles Times, San Fr</em><em>ancisco Chronicle, Seattle Times, New York magazine </em>and <em>Time magazine</em>.<strong><br />National Book Critics Award<br /></strong><strong>Best of the Month</strong> --<em>Amazon</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This is one of the spectacular audio productions of major works in our time.<strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AudioFile:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Roberto Bola&ntilde;o&rsquo;s surrealist Magnum Opus, set in Europe and South America, is divided into five books, each read here by a different Narrator, each in his way extraordinary."</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Grandiose exploration of parallel lives, secret histories, violence, death, serial killings, real life dramas and invention... but also, so much more!The last novel written by Chilean-born novelist Roberto Bola&ntilde;o depicting the unsolved and ongoing serial murders of Ciudad Ju&aacute;rez (Santa Teresa in the novel).<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; These are the same events that inspired the movie <em>Bordertown </em>with <em>Jennifer Lopez, Antonio Banderas </em>and <em>Martin Sheen</em>.<em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp; </strong>2666 </em>was greeted across Europe and Latin America as Bola&ntilde;o&rsquo;s highest achievement, surpassing even his previous work in its strangeness, beauty, and scope.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Its throng of unforgettable characters includes academics and convicts, an American sportswriter, an elusive German novelist, and a teenage student and her widowed, mentally unstable father.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Their lives intersect in the urban sprawl of Santa Teresa&mdash;a fictional Ciudad Ju&aacute;rez&mdash;on the U.S.-Mexico border, where hundreds of young factory workers in the novel, as in real life, have disappeared.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The novel is really a compendium of five parts, initially meant by Bola&ntilde;o to be a series of sequels:&nbsp;<em> The Part of the Critics; The Part of Amalfitano; The Part of Fate; The Part of Crimes; and The Part of Archimboldi </em>- all linked by varying degrees of concern with the unsolved murders.<strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial Times:</strong> "<em>As before, Bola&ntilde;o is preoccupied with parallel lives and secret histories. Largely written after 9/11, the novel manifests a new emphasis on the dangerousness of the modern world...2666<strong> </strong>is an excruciatingly challenging novel, in which Bola&ntilde;o redraws the boundaries of fiction. <br />&ldquo;It is bold in a way that few works really are &ndash; it kicks away the divide between playfulness and seriousness. And it reminds us that literature at its best inhabits what Bola&ntilde;o, with a customary wink at his own pomposity, called "the territory of risk" &ndash; it takes us to places we might not wish to go."</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; El Pa&iacute;s:</strong> <em>&ldquo;One of those strange, exquisite, and astonishing experiences that literature offers us only once in a very long time&hellip;.a writer in full pursuit of the Total Novel, one that not only completes his life&rsquo;s work but redefines it and raises it to new dizzying heights.&rdquo;</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Washington Post:</strong> <em>&ldquo;The Gabriel Garc&iacute;a M&aacute;rquez of our time: politically engaged, formally daring and wildly imaginative....[2666] should cement his reputation as a world-class novelist&hellip;.[Bola&ntilde;o] exults in his indefatigable storytelling skills and his mastery of an arsenal of styles With 2666, Bola&ntilde;o joins the ambitious overachievers of the 20th-century novel, those like Proust, Musil, Joyce, Gaddis, Pynchon, Fuentes and Vollmann, who push the novel far past its conventional size and scope to encompass an entire era, deploying encyclopedic knowledge and stylistic verve to offer a grand, if sometimes idiosyncratic summation of their culture and the novelist&rsquo;s place in it. Bola&ntilde;o has joined the immortals.&rdquo;</em><strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Amazon.com Review:</strong> <em>&ldquo;Bolano&rsquo;s true masterpiece....he writes with a horror that is both haunting and deeply humane.&rdquo;</em><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Listen to Bola&ntilde;o&rsquo;s first novel, <em>The Savage Detectives<strong> </strong></em>here<strong> www.MundoHablado.com</strong></p>', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
