(58, 3, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has appeared in films, television, and regional theaters throughout the West Coast. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For the last decade he has been a member of the resident acting company at the <em>Oregon Shakespeare Festival</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A native Californian, he divides his time between Los Angeles and Ashland, Oregon.</p>', '.png'),
(50, 41, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of numerous <em>Earphones Awards</em> and the prestigious <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> in 2006.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in England, he worked for ten years as a radio news announcer for the <em>BBC</em> and as a narrator for the <em>Royal National Institute for the Blind</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Besides narrating, he is involved in numerous stage-acting projects in the United States and Europe.</p>', '.png'),
(51, 35, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An experienced film, television, and Voice-Over actor. He has appeared most recently in the motion picture <em>Rules of Engagement </em>and on television in <em>The Practice</em> and <em>JAG</em>, as well as guest starring on many other shows.</p>', '.png'),
(53, 19, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The author of 14 best-selling books of fiction and nonfiction, all of which deal with various aspects of warfare and intelligence. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He is a radio host and former <em>CEO</em> of <em>United Press International</em> and <em>Managing Editor</em> of <em>The Sunday Times </em>(London). He was also a member of the Advisory Board of the <em>National Security Agency</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(55, 32, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A British former journalist who changed careers to become a Narrator and screen and stage actor, has performed in more than one hundred professional theater roles. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Several of his narrations have been named <em><strong>"</strong>Audio Best of the Year<strong>"</strong></em> by <em>Publishers Weekly</em>, and he has been nominated 13 times for the <em>Audie&reg; Award.</em></p>', '.png'),
(58, 56, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A northern California native, earned his <em>B.F.A. in theater from the California Institute of the Arts. </em><em><br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has worked professionally in Los Angeles as an actor and is currently in his second season with the <em>Oregon Shakespeare Festival. </em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He began recording audiobooks for family road trips at the age of 18 on his home cassette deck.</p>', '.png'),
(60, 38, '', ''),
(61, 28, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An actor, author, songwriter, and playwright. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He and his wife, Jahnna Beecham, have written more than <em>100 books</em> for teens and young readers under the name Jahnna N. Malcolm, including the best-selling series <em>The Jewel Kingdom.</em> <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Their musicals, <em>Chaps</em>! and <em>They Came from Way out There</em> (with Michael J. Hume), have played in theaters across the United States. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hillgartner&rsquo;s audiobook credits include works by<em> Dean Koontz, Nelson Algren</em>, and <em>William F. Buckley Jr</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(65, 17, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Director of <em>Blackstone&rsquo;s Audio Studios</em>, an <em>Award-winning </em>Narrator with more than <em>650 titles</em> to his credit. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Named one of the <em>Best Voices of the Century</em> and a <em>Golden Voice</em> by AudioFile. <em>Narrator of the Year</em> for 2005 by <em>Publishers Weekly</em> magazine, he was chosen  and has earned more than 20 <em>Earphones Awards</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(66, 36, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pseudonym for Simon Vance.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of numerous <em>Earphones Awards</em> and the prestigious <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> in 2006. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in England, he worked for ten years as a radio news announcer for the <em>BBC </em>and as a narrator for the <em>Royal National Institute for the Blind. </em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Besides narrating, he is involved in numerous stage-acting projects in the United States and Europe.</p>', '.png'),
(67, 39, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actor and Narrator has recorded more than two hundred audiobooks, winning 18 <em>Earphones Awards</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He was honored with an <em>Audie&reg; Award </em>in 2003 and with AudioFile magazine&rsquo;s <em>Golden Voice Award</em> in 2004.</p>', '.png'),
(68, 12, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Also known as<em> David Case</em>, (1932-2005) was one of the most prolific readers in the audiobook industry, recording more than <em>800 audiobooks</em> in his lifetime, including over two hundred for <em>Blackstone Audio</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in London, he trained at the <em>Royal Academy of Dramatic Art </em>and performed for many years in radio plays for the <em>British Broadcasting Company</em> before coming to America in 1976.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He received the AudioFile <em>Golden Voice Award </em>and numerous <em>Earphones Awards </em>and was nominated for a <em>Grammy&reg;</em> for his readings.</p>', '.png'),
(69, 12, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Also known as <em>David Case,</em> (1932-2005) was one of the most prolific readers in the audiobook industry, recording more than 800 audiobooks in his lifetime, including over two hundred for <em>Blackstone Audio</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in London, he trained at the<em> Royal Academy of Dramatic Art</em> and performed for many years in radio plays for the <em>British Broadcasting Company </em>before coming to America in 1976. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He received the <em>AudioFile Golden Voice Award</em> and numerous <em>Earphones Awards </em>and was nominated for a<em> Grammy&reg; </em>for his readings.</p>', '.png'),
(70, 12, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Also known as <em>David Case</em>, (1932-2005) was one of the most prolific readers in the audiobook industry, recording more than 800 audiobooks in his lifetime, including over two hundred for <em>Blackstone Audio</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in London, he trained at the <em>Royal Academy of Dramatic Art </em>and performed for many years in radio plays for the <em>British Broadcasting Company</em> before coming to America in 1976.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He received the <em>AudioFile Golden Voice Award </em>and numerous <em>Earphones Awards </em>and was nominated for a <em>Grammy&reg;</em> for his readings.</p>', '.png'),
(74, 37, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has played leading roles on Broadway, off Broadway, and at dozens of regional theaters throughout the country. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has a B.A. degree from Tufts University and an M.F.A. from Yale. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He now lives in Los Angeles, where he is in film and television in addition to narrating.</p>', '.png'),
(75, 31, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Was a published author, illustrator, and a Narrator of children&rsquo;s books and young adult books. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Some of the published credits of Peter Dennis include T<em>he Haunted Surfboard, Castaway, The Horror of the Heights</em>, and <em>A. A. Milne&rsquo;s Pooh Classics Boxed Set. </em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> Christopher Robin wrote: </strong><em>"Peter Dennis has made himself Pooh&rsquo;sAmbassador Extraordinary and no bear has ever had a more devoted friend. So if you want to meet the real Pooh, the bear I knew, the bear my father wrote about, listen to Peter." </em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Peter Dennis died in April of 2009.<em><br /></em></p>', '.png'),
(76, 10, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An Actress in the theater before she auditioned for audiobook Producer Stefan Rudnicki&rsquo;s<em> Skyboat Road Company </em>in Los Angeles.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She attributes her Narrator training to Rudnicki and credits him with being her audio mentor, as well as Dan Mussleman at <em>Books on Tape</em> for continuing to support her work. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Card is currently directing Stefan Rudnicki in an audio sci-fi series by Gordon R. Dickson, doing some writing for the screen (she recently Directed and starred in the Web video, "<em>Jane Austen&rsquo;s Fight Club</em>"), and finishing her first graphic novel.</p>', '.png'),
(100, 41, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of numerous <em>Earphones Awards</em> and the prestigious <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> in 2006. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in England, he worked for ten years as a radio news announcer for the <em>BBC</em> and as a narrator for the <em>Royal National Institute for the Blind.<br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Besides narrating, he is involved in numerous stage-acting projects in the United States and Europe.</p>', '.png'),
(77, 40, '', ''),
(78, 17, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Director of <em>Blackstone&rsquo;s Audio Studios</em>, an Award-winning Narrator with more than <em>650</em> titles to his credit. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Named one of the <em>Best Voices of the Century</em> and a<em> Golden Voice</em> by AudioFile magazine, <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He was chosen <em>Narrator of the Year </em>for 2005 by Publishers Weekly and has earned more than <em>20 Earphones Awards</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(79, 5, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> winning Narrator.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Received his education at Yale University, which filled out what he had already received at his mother&rsquo;s knee in the all-important areas of Shakespeare, Greek art and architecture, and the Italian Renaissance.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He restores Greek Revival buildings and appears in television, film, and on stage whenever the pilasters and entablatures overwhelm him.</p>', '.png'),
(80, 17, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Director of Blackstone&rsquo;s Audio Studios</em>, an Award-winning Narrator with more than <em>650</em> titles to his credit. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Named one of the <em>Best Voices of the Century</em> and a <em>Golden Voice</em> by AudioFile magazine.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He was chosen <em>Narrator of the Year</em> for 2005 by Publishers Weekly and has earned more than <em>20 Earphones Awards</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(81, 33, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has appeared in numerous films and television shows, including <em>Frasier, ER, Will &amp; Grace</em>, <em>The Suite Life of Zack, Cody</em>, and<em> Almost Famous</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A 15 year&nbsp;veteran of the <em>Oregon Shakespeare Festival</em>, he lives in Los Angeles with his wife and son.</p>', '.png'),
(82, 39, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actor and Narrator Scott Brick has recorded more than <em>200 </em>audiobooks, winning <em>18 Earphones Awards</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He was honored with an <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> in 2003 and with AudioFile magazine&rsquo;s <em>Golden Voice Award</em> in 2004.</p>', '.png'),
(83, 46, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Earphones</em> winner, <em>Audie&reg; </em>nominee, and <em>Parent&rsquo;s Choice Award</em> winning Producer, Tavia Gilbert is a classical theater- and public radio-trained Actress and Producer. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She makes her home in Portland, Maine, where she works as a Writer and a stage and Voice actoress. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She produces, directs, and narrates unique audiobooks, full-cast recordings, and documentaries.</p>', '.png'),
(84, 22, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2009 <em>Best Voice in Fiction&amp; Classics</em>: for <em>The Count of Monte Cristo</em> (also here at <strong>www.MundoHablado.com</strong>)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2008 <em>Best Voice in Fiction &amp; Classics: for </em><em>The Solitude of Thomas Cave</em><strong><em> </em></strong>and&nbsp;<em>The White Tiger</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has read more than a <em>100 audiobooks</em> of every conceivable genre, including the numerous Bestsellers<strong>,</strong> notably those by the author<strong> </strong><em>Ken Follet</em>.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In Southern California he has acted in productions at the <em>Mark Taper Forum, A Noise Within,</em> and <em>The Globe Theaters </em>in San Diego. He has also been seen on the stages of all of Seattle&rsquo;s major theaters as well as the <em>Tacoma Actors Guild </em>and the <em>New Mexico Rep.</em></p>', '.png'),
(85, 22, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2009 <em>Best Voice in Fiction&amp; Classics: for The Count of Monte Cristo</em> (here at <strong>www.MundoHablado.com</strong>)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2008 <em>Best Voice in Fiction &amp; Classics: for The Solitude of Thomas Cave </em>and&nbsp;The White Tiger.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has read more than a<em> 100 </em>audiobooks of every conceivable genre, including the numerous Bestsellers, notably those by the author Ken Follet.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In Southern California he has acted in productions at the <em>Mark Taper Forum, A Noise Within</em>, and<em> The Globe Theaters </em>in San Diego. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has also been seen on the stages of all of Seattle&rsquo;s major theaters as well as the T<em>acoma Actors Guild</em> and the <em>New Mexico Rep</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(86, 32, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Also known as <em>Geoffrey Howard</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A British former journalist who changed careers to become a Narrator and screen and stage actor, has performed in more than one hundred professional theater roles. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Several of his narrations have been named "<em>Audio Best of the Year</em>" by <em>Publishers Weekly</em>, and he has been nominated 13 times for the <em>Audie&reg; Award</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(87, 17, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Also known as <em>Tom Parker</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He is Director of Blackstone&rsquo;s Audio Studios, an Award-winning Narrator with more than <em>650</em> titles to his credit.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Named one of the <em>Best Voices of the Century </em>and a<em> Golden Voice</em> by AudioFile magazine, he was chosen <em>Narrator of the Year</em> for 2005 by <em>Publishers Weekly</em> and has earned more than <em>20 Earphones Awards</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Narrator&rsquo;s Comments:</strong> <em>"It&rsquo;s terrible to say that the Nazi era is fascinating, but it is. Yet, more importantly, we learn how short a slope it is to the sort of brutality and mindless belief in authority that took hold of people at that time."</em></p>', '.png'),
(88, 24, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Stage actress Kate Reading has been a Freelance Narrator for over 20 years. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She has received an <em>Audie Award</em> and 2 <em>Audie</em> nominations, as well as numerous <em>Earphones Awards</em> from <em>AudioFile</em> magazine, which has named her Narrator of the Year, and for two years running, B<em>est Voice in Science Fiction and Fantasy</em> for her narration of Jim Butcher&rsquo;s Codex Alera Series. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the Science Fiction genre she is also the Narrator of all of Robert Jordan&rsquo;s titles of the <em>Wheel of Time Series</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(90, 41, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of numerous<em> Earphones Awards</em> and the prestigious <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> in 2006. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in England, he worked for ten years as a radio news announcer for the <em>BBC</em> and as a narrator for the <em>Royal National Institute for the Blind. <br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Besides narrating, he is involved in numerous stage-acting projects in the United States and Europe.</p>', '.png'),
(91, 50, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A <em>Professor of Political Science at Southern Oregon University</em> in Ashland, Oregon. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He received his doctorate in American politics from the<em> University of California, Davis. </em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has done <em>Voice-Over</em> work for radio and film and is also an accomplished jazz guitarist.</p>', ''),
(89, 4, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of <em>6 AudioFile Earphones Awards</em> and has twice been nominated for the prestigious <em>Audie&reg; Award</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She studied at the <em>Royal National Theatre</em> in London and <em>The Studio Theater</em> in Washington, D.C., and has appeared at the <em>Kennedy Center </em>and <em>off Broadway. <br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She lives in Brooklyn, New York.</p>', '.png'),
(92, 25, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has appeared in many films, including <em>The Dark Knight, Missing,</em> and <em>A Perfect World</em>, and on such television shows as <em>The Equalizer, Angel, Cold Case, Golden Years</em>, and <em>Profit</em> . <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Szarabajka has also appeared in several episodes of Selected Stories for National Public Radio. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He won the 2001 <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> for<em> Unabridged Fiction</em> for his reading of <em>Tom Robbins&rsquo; Fierce Invalids Home from Hot Climates. <strong><br /></strong></em></p>', '.png'),
(97, 3, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has appeared in films, television, and regional theaters throughout the West Coast. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For the last decade he has been a member of the resident acting company at the <em>Oregon Shakespeare Festival</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A native Californian, he divides his time between Los Angeles and Ashland, Oregon.</p>', '.png'),
(93, 43, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has narrated<strong> </strong>more than<strong> </strong><em>100</em> audiobooks. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A recipient of multiple <em>AudioFile Earphones Awards,</em> a <em>Grammy</em><strong>&reg;-</strong>winning <em>Audiobook Producer</em> and received the coveted<em> Audie&reg; Award </em>in 2005.</p>', '.png'),
(94, 7, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An actress and singer with extensive experience on both the theater and concert stages.</p>', '.png'),
(93, 10, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An Actress in the theater before she auditioned for audiobook Producer Stefan Rudnicki&rsquo;s Skyboat Road Company in Los Angeles.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She attributes her narrator training to Rudnicki and credits him with being her audio mentor, as well as Dan Mussleman at Books on Tape for continuing to support her work. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Card is currently directing Stefan Rudnicki in an audio sci-fi series by Gordon R. Dickson, doing some writing for the screen (she recently Directedstarred in the Web video, "<em>Jane Austen&rsquo;s Fight Club</em>"), and finishing her first graphic novel. and</p>', '.png'),
(95, 23, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has narrated more than <em>40</em> audiobooks, been nominated for a prestigious <em>Audie Award</em>, and has received <em>4 AudioFile Earphones Awards</em>, including one for <em>My Kind of Place</em> by Susan Orlean.<em><strong><br /></strong></em></p>', '.png'),
(96, 27, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Named as one of <em>AudioFile</em> magazine&rsquo;s <em>Best Voices of the Year,</em> has received numerous <em>Audie Award </em>nominations and <em>AudioFile Earphones</em> awards for her narrations. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An experienced stage actress, she has also guest-starred on many top television series and stars in Director Sam Raimi&rsquo;s film<em> Drag Me to Hell</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(98, 53, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She has hosted <em>Marian McPartland&rsquo;s Piano Jazz on National Public Radio</em> since 1979. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She has many recordings to her credit and continues to perform in the United States.</p>', '.png'),
(99, 32, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Also known as&nbsp;Geoffrey Howard. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>A British former journalist who changed careers to become a Narrator and screen and stage actor, has performed in more than one hundred professional theater roles. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Several of his narrations have been named <em>Audio Best of the Year</em> by Publishers Weekly, and he has been nominated 13 times for the <em>Audie&reg; Award</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(172, 35, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An experienced film, television, and Voice-Over actor. He has appeared  most recently in the motion picture <em>Rules of Engagement </em>and on  television in <em>The Practice</em> and <em>JAG</em>, as well as guest  starring on many other shows.</p>', '.png'),
(46, 17, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Also known as Tom Parker, he is an award-winning<strong> </strong>Narrator with more than<em> 650 </em>titles to his credit. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Named one of the "<em>Best Voices of the Century"</em> and a <em>Golden Voice </em>by AudioFilemagazine and he was chosen <em>Narrator of the Year</em> for 2005 by Publishers Weekly. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has earned more than 25 <em>Earphones Awards</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(47, 34, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An actor-director in the theater, a poet and a documentary filmmaker. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He is also a jazz trombonist whose jazz quartet, Leatherstocking, gets its name from one of his favorite<em> Blackstone Audio</em> narrations: The Deerslayer.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He lives in New York</p>', '.png'),
(108, 58, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Puertorrique&ntilde;a<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>Para el mercado internacional latinoamericano trabaj&oacute; durante d&eacute;cadas como productora/animadora/narradora de<em> Worldnet TV</em> y la <em>Voz de Am&eacute;rica.<br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A trav&eacute;s de los a&ntilde;os ha grabado para, entre otros, <em>National Geographic, Discovery Channel, Biblioteca del Congreso de los Estados Unidos, Banco Mundial, Departamento de Educaci&oacute;n de los Estados Unidos, Oficina del Censo de los Estados Unidos, Cruz Roja Internacional, Simon &amp; Schuster, Santillana Publishing &ndash; USA, UNESCO, Random House, Recorded Books y National Institutes of Health.</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En calidad de productora y animadora, trabaj&oacute; para los canales de TV en Washington, D.C. afiliados a la <em>ABC, CBS</em> y<em> NBC.&nbsp; <br /></em></p>', '.png'),
(108, 59, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Argentino<br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Locutor nacional, egresado del Instituto Superior de Ense&ntilde;anza Radiof&oacute;nica (ISER) y Traductor P&uacute;blico de franc&eacute;s, egresado de la Universidad de Buenos Aires (UBA).<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Como locutor, ha trabajado en Radio Ciudad, Radio Am&eacute;rica y Radio del Plata de Buenos Aires. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actualmente, realiza grabaciones de spots publicitarios, videos institucionales y cursos de capacitaci&oacute;n para las principales empresas proveedoras de e-learning de los mercados argentino, latinoamericano y espa&ntilde;ol.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Desde 2002, se desempe&ntilde;a como traductor de &ldquo;<em>Le Monde diplomatique</em>&rdquo;, para sus ediciones del Cono Sur, Espa&ntilde;a, M&eacute;xico, Chile, Colombia y Bolivia.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Es adem&aacute;s docente de la Carrera de Locuci&oacute;n de la Universidad de Ciencias Empresariales y Sociales (UCES).<strong><br /></strong></p>', '.png'),
(44, 26, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hails from the Midwest. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He received his B.A. in theater from a small liberal-arts college in New Mexico. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He acts in the theater when his schedule permits and spends much of his free time working in his garden. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He lives in Virginia with his wife and son.</p>', '.png'),
(45, 43, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A <em>Grammy</em>-winning audiobook producer. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has narrated more than 100 audiobooks. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A recipient of multiple <em>AudioFile Earphones Awards</em>, he was awarded the coveted <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> for solo narration in both 2005 and 2007, and was named as one of<em> AudioFile&rsquo;s Best Voices of the Year </em>in 2008.</p>', '.png'),
(109, 60, '<p><em>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Argentino</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Durante m&aacute;s de una d&eacute;cada viene desempe&ntilde;&aacute;ndose como locutor en radio, televisi&oacute;n y publicidad, especializ&aacute;ndose en la personificaci&oacute;n de distintas voces.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Trabaja como actor de doblaje para las principales cadenas de televisi&oacute;n en documentales, series, pel&iacute;culas y dibujos animados que han incluido, entre otros, <em>Power Rangers, Ugly Betty, Mythbusters, American Chopper, Las aventuras de Merlin, Gaturro y El lince perdido.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em></p>', ''),
(3, 18, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She excels in portraying the main character&rsquo;s shotgun-toting attitude, her husband&rsquo;s farm family expressions and the snobbishness of upper crust society.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The entire book is filled with hysterically funny dialogues and inspired views on life.</p>', '.png'),
(4, 21, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has appeared both on and <em>off </em><em>Broadway</em><strong> </strong>as well as in hundreds of radio and television commercials.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has earned multiple <em>AudioFile Earphones Awards</em> and has been nominated for the prestigious<strong> </strong><em>Audie&reg; Award</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(5, 11, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A graduate of the <em>London Academy of Music and Dramatic Art</em>, Fred Williams works in theater, film, television, and radio in England, Ireland, and America.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Besides narrating audiobooks, he is a performer in living-history reenactments, an archer, and a poet.</p>', '.png'),
(7, 21, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has appeared both on and <em>off Broadway</em> as well as in hundreds of radio and television commercials.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has narrated books by such authors as<strong> </strong><em>Larry McMurtry, </em><em>Jay McInerney</em>, and <em>Andy McNab</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has earned multiple <em>AudioFile Earphones Awards</em> and has been nominated for the prestigious <em>Audie&reg; Award</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(9, 42, '<p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SFFAudio.com:</strong> "Robinson<em> reads in such a comfortable, personable way that it&rsquo;s easy to imagine that this guy you know popped in for lunch and is telling you this story over the kitchen table."</em></p>', '.png'),
(10, 3, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has appeared in films, television, and regional theaters throughout the West Coast.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For the last decade he has been a member of the resident acting company at the <em>Oregon Shakespeare Festival</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A native Californian, he divides his time between Los Angeles and Ashland, Oregon.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; With impeccable fluency in both English and Spanish, Narrator Armando Dur&aacute;n carries the listeners to the Latin ambience of the book and keeps them riveted throughout the 37 hours of the storytelling.</p>', '.png'),
(12, 2, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has earned <strong>Tony</strong> nominations and an <em>Obie Award </em>for his theater work. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has had guest appearances in television&rsquo;s <em>Law &amp; Order, The X-Files, Miami Vice</em>, and <em>Boston Public</em> and starred as Dr. Frederick Chilton in the 1991 <em>Oscar&reg;</em><strong>-</strong>winning film <em>Silence of the Lambs. <br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He lives in Ashland, Oregon, with his family.</p>', '.png'),
(14, 8, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Veteran Actor and Narrator currently appears on <em>The Wire</em> on <em>HBO</em> and narrates The First 48<em><strong> </strong></em>on <em>A&amp;E</em>, as well as various projects for the <em>BBC</em> and <em>PBS</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has performed on and <em>off Broadway</em>, in films, and in several hit television series.</p>', '.png'),
(109, 58, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Puertorrique&ntilde;a</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Para el mercado internacional latinoamericano trabaj&oacute; durante d&eacute;cadas como productora/animadora/narradora de <em>Worldnet TV</em> y la <em>Voz de Am&eacute;rica</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A trav&eacute;s de los a&ntilde;os ha grabado para, entre otros, <em>National Geographic, Discovery Channel, Biblioteca del Congreso de los Estados Unidos, Banco Mundial, Departamento de Educaci&oacute;n de los Estados Unidos, Oficina del Censo de los Estados Unidos, Cruz Roja Internacional, Simon &amp; Schuster, Santillana Publishing &ndash; USA, UNESCO, Random House, Recorded Books y National Institutes of Health.</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En calidad de productora y animadora, trabaj&oacute; para los canales de TV en Washington, D.C. afiliados a la <em>ABC, CBS y NBC.</em> <em><br /></em></p>', ''),
(174, 54, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has appeared in films, television, and regional theaters throughout the  West Coast. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For the last decade he has been a member of the  resident acting company at the <em>Oregon Shakespeare Festival</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  A native Californian, he divides his time between Los Angeles and  Ashland, Oregon.</p>', '.png'),
(190, 74, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nacida en Brazil, criada en M&eacute;xico, y durante su carrera  profesional, residente en Nueva York.&nbsp; <br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; La galardonada actriz con numerosas apariciones en teatro,  televisi&oacute;n y cine.&nbsp; Es trilingue trabajando en espa&ntilde;ol, portugu&eacute;s e  ingl&eacute;s.<br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Entre sus cr&eacute;ditos en ingl&eacute;s se incluyen programas de TV y  pel&iacute;culas tales como:<em> Law &amp; Order, The Ministers, Shut Up and Do  It!, Empire, One Night Stand, Destiny Has No Favorites</em> y <em>Total  Recall.</em></p>', '.png'),
(37, 36, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of numerous <em>Earphones Awards</em> and the prestigious <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> in 2006. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in England, he worked for ten years as a radio news announcer for the <em>BBC</em> and as a narrator for the<em> Royal National Institute for the Blind. <br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Besides narrating, he is involved in numerous stage-acting projects in the United States and Europe."</p>', '.png'),
(110, 61, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Argentino.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Locutor, actor y profesional de doblaje para radio y televisi&oacute;n. &nbsp;<br />Narrador para documentales, entre otros, de <em>Discovery Channel, FOX Sports . The History Channel, A&amp;E, Comit&eacute; Internacional de la Cruz Roja&nbsp; e Infinito TV.&nbsp; <br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Locutor de promociones de los canales regionals USA Network, Fox Kidds, J&eacute;tric y DLA (Digital Latin America).<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ha doblado largometrajes, series, dibujos animados (<em>Cars, Los Pint&iacute;n al rescate, Micaela, Patoruzito</em>, entre otras.) y de animaci&oacute;n especial como la multipremiada internacionalmente <em>&ldquo;Viaje a Marte&rdquo;.<br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Es conductor de radio en FM LATINA y CADENA LATINA en Buenos Aires y la voz institucional y art&iacute;stica de CADENA TOP 40.</p>', '.png'),
(111, 62, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Argentino&nbsp; </em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Estudi&oacute; actuaci&oacute;n dram&aacute;tica en la Universidad del Centro, Tandi y la Escuela de Arte Dram&aacute;tico de Mar del Plata. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Estudios de Carrera de Locutor Nacional en el Instituto Superior de Ense&ntilde;anza Radiof&oacute;nica (ISER), Mar del Plata.&nbsp; Estudios de Doblaje, Castellano Neutro y Formaci&oacute;n Actoral en Buenos Aires.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ha trabajado como locutor para el Canal 7, el Canal de Musica Much Music<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ha grabado comerciales de radio y TV para marcas tales como: <em>Zurich Seguros, Banco Ciudad, Movistar, Nestum, Ameircan Airlines, Kodak, Prosegur Activa, ADT, Lo Jack Home, Banco de Bogot&aacute;,</em> entre otros.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tambi&eacute;n doblaje de programas de televisi&oacute;n para empresas tales como Animal Planet<em>.</em> y<em> Discovery Channel</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Conductor de radio en Pop Radio 101.5.</p>', '.png'),
(196, 63, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Argentino</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Egresado de la Escuela Nacional de Arte Dram&atilde;tico.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actor de teatro y TV.&nbsp; Actualmente participa en el ciclo de radioteatro de Radio Nacional Las dos car&atilde;tulas,dirigido y producido por Nora Massi.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A nivel internacional ha hecho cu&ntilde;as publicitarias, entre otros, para:<em><br />Bud Light </em><em>(EE.UU)-Banco de Chile </em><em>(CHILE) - KUMIX Alpina </em><em>(COLOMBIA) - Quesos BONDIA (COLOMBIA)- Sprint (EE.UU) - Peugeot 206 (FRANCIA)- Automovil Club Argentino - Supermercados DISCO (URUGUAY)- Home Depot(EE.UU.) - Banco AV Villas (COLOMBIA) - Corbanca (CHILE) - Serfin Light (MEXICO) - Telnor (MEXICO) - Galavisi&oacute;n (MEXICO) - JUMEX Cerveza Sol (MEXICO)- &ndash; FBTO (HOLANDA) &ndash; BCO VillasARCAEX (EE.UU.) &ndash; Direct-TV (EE.UU.) &ndash; Seguros Bolivar Expedia (ALEMANIA) &ndash;BITBURGER (ALEMANIA).</em><em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em> Tuvo a cargo el doblaje de Arnold Schwarzenegger en<em> "El &uacute;ltimo gran h&eacute;roe"</em><em>, </em>Brad Pitt en<em> </em><em>"Kalifornia", </em>Hugh Grant en<em> "</em><em>Cuatro bodas y un funeral" y </em>Christopher Lambert en<em> "</em><em>Highlander 2". <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em> En la actualidad realiza doblajes de documentales para<em> Infinito - ISAT Discovery Channel, People &amp; Arts y Animal Planet.</em></p>', '.png'),
(28, 41, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of numerous <em>Earphones Awards</em> and the prestigious <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> in 2006.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in England, he worked for ten years as a radio news announcer for the <em>BBC</em> and as a narrator for the <em>Royal National Institute for the Blind</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Besides narrating, he is involved in numerous stage-acting projects in the United States and Europe.</p>', '.png'),
(35, 11, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A graduate of the <em>London Academy of Music and Dramatic Art</em>, he works in theater, film, television, and radio in England, Ireland, and America. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Besides narrating audiobooks, he is a performer in living-history reenactments, an archer and a poet.</p>', '.png'),
(36, 15, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A <em>Grammy</em>-nominated and award-winning audio producer.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; She has narrated dozens of audiobooks and is a recipient of multiple <em>AudioFile Earphones Awards</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Her extensive stage and screen credits include the major motion picture <em>The American President.</em></p>', '.png'),
(113, 64, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Argentino</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Egresado del <strong>ISER</strong> con el t&iacute;tulo de<strong> Locutor  Profesional Nacional</strong>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Se desempe&ntilde;a a <em>nivel nacional e internacional </em>como <em>actor</em> publicitario, <em>voz </em>de identificaci&oacute;n de marcas, actor de doblaje y  <em>locutor/narrador de radio y televisi&oacute;n</em>.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Entre sus cr&eacute;ditos se encuentran:&nbsp; <em>Discovery Channel, National  Geographic, Animal Planet, America TV, Radio Mitre, Cronica TV y Canal  13.</em></p>', '.png');
