(115, 58, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Puertorrique&ntilde;a<br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Para el mercado  internacional latinoamericano trabaj&oacute; durante d&eacute;cadas como productora/animadora/narradora de <em>Worldnet TV</em> y la <em>Voz de Am&eacute;rica</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A trav&eacute;s de  los a&ntilde;os ha grabado para, entre otros, <em>National Geographic, Discovery  Channel, Biblioteca del Congreso de los Estados Unidos, Banco Mundial,  Departamento de Educaci&oacute;n de los Estados Unidos, Oficina del Censo de  los Estados Unidos, Cruz Roja Internacional, Simon &amp; Schuster,  Santillana Publishing &ndash; USA, UNESCO, Random House, Recorded Books y National  Institutes of Health.</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En calidad de productora y  animadora, trabaj&oacute; para los canales de TV en Washington, D.C.  afiliados a la <em>ABC, CBS y NBC.</em></p>', '.png'),
(23, 43, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A <em>Grammy</em>-winning audiobook Producer. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has narrated more than <em>100 audiobooks. <br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A recipient of multiple <em>AudioFile Earphones Awards</em>, he was awarded the coveted <em>Audie&reg; Award </em>for solo narration in both 2005 and 2007, and was named as one of <em>AudioFile&rsquo;s Best Voices of the Year </em>in 2008.</p>', '.png'),
(24, 43, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A <em>Grammy</em>-winning audiobook Producer. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has narrated more than 100 audiobooks. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A recipient of multiple <em>AudioFile Earphones Awards</em>, he was awarded the coveted <em>Audie&reg; Award </em>for solo narration in both 2005 and 2007, and was named as one of <em>AudioFile&rsquo;s Best Voices of the Year</em> in 2008.</p>', '.png'),
(116, 58, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Puertorrique&ntilde;a<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>Para el mercado internacional latinoamericano trabaj&oacute; durante d&eacute;cadas como productora/animadora/narradora de<em> Worldnet TV</em> y la <em>Voz de Am&eacute;rica.</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A trav&eacute;s de los a&ntilde;os ha grabado para, entre otros, National Geographic, Discovery Channel, Biblioteca del Congreso de los Es<em>tados Unidos, Banco Mundial, Departamento de Educaci&oacute;n de los Estados Unidos, Oficina del Censo de los Estados Unidos, Cruz Roja Internacional, Simon &amp; Schuster, Santillana Publishing &ndash; USA, UNESCO, Random House, Recorded Books y National Institutes of Health.<br /></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En calidad de productora y animadora, trabaj&oacute; para los canales de TV en Washington, D.C. afiliados a la<em> ABC, CBS y NBC.&nbsp; <br /></em></p>', '.png'),
(171, 54, '<p>Has appeared in films, television, and regional theaters throughout the  West Coast. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For the last decade he has been a member of the  resident acting company at the<em> Oregon Shakespeare Festival</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  A native Californian, he divides his time between Los Angeles and  Ashland, Oregon.</p>', '.png'),
(167, 54, '<p>Has appeared in films, television, and regional theaters throughout the  West Coast.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For the last decade he has been a member of the  resident acting company at the <em>Oregon Shakespeare Festival</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  A native Californian, he divides his time between Los Angeles and  Ashland, Oregon.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; With impeccable fluency in both English and  Spanish, Narrator Armando Dur&aacute;n carries the listeners to the Latin  ambience of the book and keeps them riveted throughout the 37 hours of  the storytelling.</p>', '.jpg'),
(169, 51, '<p>A published Narrator of children&rsquo;s books. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Some of his the  published credits with Library Edition include <em>The Voyages of Doctor  Dolittle, For the Temple </em>and <em>The Young Carthaginian</em>.</p>', ''),
(170, 49, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Attended the <em>University of Southern Maine</em> in Portland-Gorham  before pursuing a career in voice work in<em> London</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has  garnered 13 <em>Earphones Awards</em> and was voted one of "<em>The Best  Voices at the End of the Century</em>" by AudioFile magazine.</p>', '.png'),
(117, 65, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actriz y Narradora, fue una de las integrantes de la compa&ntilde;&iacute;a de teatro <em>&ldquo;Repertorio espa&ntilde;ol&rdquo; </em>en la ciudad de Nueva York durante 10 a&ntilde;os. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ganadora del<em> Premio Audie 2010</em> en la categor&iacute;a de Audiolibros en espa&ntilde;ol por su narraci&oacute;n de <em>&ldquo;La traves&iacute;a de Enrique&rdquo;</em> de Sonia Nazario, producido por Recorded Books.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tambi&eacute;n recibi&oacute; una beca de la Fundaci&oacute;n Princess Grace; el premio como la <em>Mejor Artista en el Festival de Chamizal</em>, El Paso, por su actuaci&oacute;n en <em>&ldquo;El burlador de Sevilla&rdquo;</em>; y el premio <em>ACE</em> por su actuaci&oacute;n en <em>&ldquo;Revoltillo&rdquo;</em> de Eduardo Machado.</p>', '.png'),
(11, 51, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A published Narrator of children&rsquo;s books. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Some of his the  published credits with Library Edition include <em>The Voyages of Doctor  Dolittle, For the Temple </em>and <em>The Young Carthaginian</em>.</p>', ''),
(118, 66, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actor, Director, Narrador y Locutor.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cuenta con una Maestr&iacute;a en Comunicaciones y un t&iacute;tulo universitario en Arte Dram&aacute;tico.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En Nueva York complet&oacute; otra Maestr&iacute;a en Teatro Educativo de la Universidad de Nueva York.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En el 2010 fue nominado al prestigioso <em>Premio Audie </em>en la catagor&iacute;a de audiolibro en espa&ntilde;ol por su narraci&oacute;n en dos producciones de Recorded Books:&nbsp; <em>&ldquo;El juego del angel&rdquo; </em>de Carlos Ruiz Zaf&oacute;n, y <em>&ldquo;&iquest;Por qu&eacute; ese idiota es rico y yo&nbsp; no?</em> de Robert Shemin.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sus cr&eacute;ditos teatrales incluyen muchas producciones del <em>Spanish Repertory Theatre</em> en Nueva York y otros teatros hispanos.&nbsp; Ha actuado en obras teatrales tales como <em>&ldquo;A Man&rsquo;s a Man&rdquo;</em> de Brecht.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En televisi&oacute;n ha tenido apariciones en <em>&ldquo;The Cosby Show</em>&rdquo; y varias telenovelas. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ha grabado decenas de audiolibros para Recorded Books y la American Foundation for the Blind.</p>', '.png'),
(165, 28, '<p>Actor, author, songwriter, and playwright.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He and his wife,  Jahnna Beecham, have written more than 100 books for teens and young  readers under the name Jahnna N. Malcolm, including the best-selling  series <em>The Jewel Kingdom. Their musicals, Chaps!</em> and <em>They Came  from Way out There</em> (with Michael J. Hume), have played in theaters  across the United States.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hillgartner&rsquo;s audiobook credits  include works by<em> Dean Koontz, Nelson Algren</em>, and<em> William F.  Buckley Jr</em></p>\r\n<p>.</p>', '.png'),
(166, 47, '<p>A dialogue director and voice artist best known for his voice roles in  CD-ROM games and<strong> </strong>TV shows such as <em>Buffy the Vampire Slayer </em>and  <em>Transformers</em>.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He is a former member of the <em>Oregon  Shakespeare Festival.</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An <em>Earphones Award</em> winner and <em>Audie&reg;  Award </em>nominee. He has narrated more than 100 books for<em> Blackstone Audio</em></p>\r\n<p>.</p>', '.png'),
