(158, 66, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actor, Director, Narrador y Locutor.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cuenta con una  Maestr&iacute;a en Comunicaciones y un t&iacute;tulo universitario en Arte Dram&aacute;tico.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  En Nueva York complet&oacute; otra <em>Maestr&iacute;a en Teatro Educativo</em> de la <em>Universidad  de Nueva York</em>.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En el 2010 fue nominado al prestigioso <em>Premio  Audie </em>en la catagor&iacute;a de audiolibro en espa&ntilde;ol por su narraci&oacute;n en  dos producciones de Recorded Books:&nbsp; &ldquo;<em>El juego del angel</em>&rdquo; de  Carlos Ruiz Zaf&oacute;n, y &ldquo;<em>&iquest;Por qu&eacute; ese idiota es rico y yo&nbsp; no?</em>" de  Robert Shemin.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sus cr&eacute;ditos teatrales incluyen muchas  producciones del <em>Spanish Repertory Theatre</em> en Nueva York y otros  teatros hispanos.&nbsp; Ha actuado en obras teatrales tales como &ldquo;<em>A Man&rsquo;s a  Man</em>&rdquo; de Brecht.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En televisi&oacute;n ha tenido apariciones en &ldquo;<em>The  Cosby Show</em>&rdquo; y varias telenovelas. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ha grabado decenas de  audiolibros para <em>Recorded Books </em>y la <em>American Foundation for  the Blind.</em></p>', '.png'),
(160, 79, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actor y productor nacido en Saltillo, M&eacute;xico.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Es ingeniero mec&aacute;nico industrial graduado del ITESM, recinto de Monterrey.&nbsp; Pero se mud&oacute; a Austin, Tejas donde obtuvo una Maestr&iacute;a en Arte de la Universidad de Texas.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ha trabajado en Estados Unidos en teatro, televisi&oacute;n, cine y radio y actualmente reside en Nueva York.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En sus trabajos como narrador hizo la voz del Mago en la pel&iacute;cula del Mago de Oz de HBO, asi como varios personajes en la pel&iacute;cula, tambi&eacute;n de HBO, de Never Ending Story.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ha recibido el Premio de Mejor Actor de la Asociaci&oacute;n Hispana de Actores Latinos en USA, y premios como mejor actor por sus actuaciones en varias obras de teatro.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Domina el ingl&eacute;s, espa&ntilde;ol, portugu&eacute;s e italiano.</p>', '.jpg'),
(162, 86, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actriz de cine y poeta.</p>', '.png'),
(161, 66, '<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em> Actor, Director, Narrador y Locutor.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cuenta con una Maestr&iacute;a en Comunicaciones y un t&iacute;tulo universitario en Arte Dram&aacute;tico.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En Nueva York complet&oacute; otra Maestr&iacute;a en Teatro Educativo de la Universidad de Nueva York.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En el 2010 fue nominado al prestigioso Premio Audie en la catagor&iacute;a de audiolibro en espa&ntilde;ol por su narraci&oacute;n en dos producciones de Recorded Books:&nbsp; &ldquo;<em>El juego del angel</em>&rdquo; de Carlos Ruiz Zaf&oacute;n, y &ldquo;<em>&iquest;Por qu&eacute; ese idiota es rico y yo&nbsp; no?</em>" de Robert Shemin.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sus cr&eacute;ditos teatrales incluyen muchas producciones del Spanish Repertory Theatre en Nueva York y otros teatros hispanos.&nbsp; Ha actuado en obras teatrales tales como &ldquo;<em>A Man&rsquo;s a Man</em>&rdquo; de Brecht.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; En televisi&oacute;n ha tenido apariciones en &ldquo;<em>The Cosby Show</em>&rdquo; y varias telenovelas. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ha grabado decenas de audiolibros para <em>Recorded Books</em> y la <em>American Foundation for the Blind.</em></p>', '.png'),
(163, 57, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He lends <em>&rsquo;The Part about Fate&rsquo;</em> a deadpan humor.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A&nbsp; longtime member of the acting company at the <em>Oregon Shakespeare Festival</em>, has also been a faculty member at <em>The Johnny Carson School of Film and Television</em> at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; His voice may also be heard on a number of video games and advertisements for radio and television.</p>', ''),
(163, 39, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; His characters&rsquo; voices are outstanding.!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actor and Narrator Scott Brick has recorded more than <em>200 audiobooks, </em>winning <em>18 Earphones Awards. </em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He was honored with an <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> in 2003 and with <em>AudioFile</em> magazine&rsquo;s <em>Golden Voice Award</em> in 2004.</p>', '.png'),
(163, 22, '<p><span lang="EN-US"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><em>Best Voice in Fiction &amp; Classics: for The Count of Monte Cristo</em> (also here at <em>www.MundoHablado.com</em>)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2008 <em>Best Voice in Fiction &amp; Classics</em>: for&nbsp;<em>The Solitude of Thomas Cave</em> and <em>The White Tiger.</em> <br /></span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has read more than a </span><em><span lang="EN-US">100</span></em><span lang="EN-US"><em> </em>audiobooks of every conceivable genre, including the numerous Bestsellers authored by Ken Follet.</span></p>', '.png'),
(163, 17, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; As <em>Director of Blackstone&rsquo;s Audio Studios</em>, Gardner took over a month just to audition and cast the book. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He is himself an Award-winning Narrator with more than <em>650</em> titles to his credit.&nbsp; In this production Grover narrates the saga of the writer Benno von Archimboldi at a compelling pace.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Named one of the <em>Best Voices of the Century</em> and a <em>Golden Voice</em> by <em>AudioFile </em>magazine, he was chosen <em>Narrator of the Year</em> for 2005 by Publishers Weekly and has earned more than <em>20 Earphones Awards.</em></p>', '.png'),
(163, 54, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Brings his mostly Spanish-flavored section to vivid life.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; With impeccable fluency in both English and Spanish, Narrator Armando Duran carries the listeners to the Latin ambience of the book and keeps&nbsp; them riveted throughout the 32 hours of the storytelling. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has appeared in films, television, and regional theaters throughout the West Coast. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For the last decade he has been a member of the resident acting company at the <em>Oregon Shakespeare Festival</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A native Californian, he divides his time between Los Angeles and Ashland, Oregon.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '.png'),
(159, 78, '', ''),
(49, 22, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He has read more than a 100 audiobooks of every conceivable genre. In Southern California he has acted in productions at the Mark Taper Forum, A Noise Within, and <em>The Globe Theaters in San Diego</em>. <br />He has also been seen on the stages of all of Seattle&rsquo;s major theaters as well as the <em>Tacoma Actors Guild</em> and the <em>New Mexico Rep</em>.</p>', '.png'),
(59, 14, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Incorporated in 1993, <em>The Hollywood Theater of the Ear</em> is a non-profit corporation dedicated exclusively to the production, encouragement and appreciation of <em>world-class audio drama</em> for descriminating audiences.</p>', '.png'),
(62, 41, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of numerous <em>Earphones Awards</em> and the prestigious <em>Audie&reg; Award</em> in 2006. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Born in England, he worked for ten years as a radio news announcer for the <em>BBC</em> and as a narrator for the <em>Royal National Institute for the Blind</em>. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Besides narrating, he is involved in numerous stage-acting projects in the United States and Europe.</p>', '.png'),
(63, 45, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winner of the 2007 <em>Audie&reg; Award for Best Narration </em>by the Author. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Of his 11 novels, T<em>he Tortilla Curtain i</em>s his most successful one. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He lives with his family near Santa Barbara, California.</p>', '.png');
